title: chicken and sauerkraut
directions: Spread sauerkraut in bottom of baking dish.
Put chicken in next.
Cover with sliced cheese.
Add Italian dressing. Refrigerate one hour.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: deluxe pot roast
directions: Sprinkle beef with salt and pepper.
Brown on stove top on all sides, about 15 minutes.
Chop onion and sprinkle over roast. Combine sour cream and flour.
Pour over roast.
Add wine.
Cook for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: neckbones and yellow rice
directions: Wash neckbones and put in a heavy pot. Cover with water. Add all ingredients, except rice. Cook until tender. Add rice and cook briskly for 5 to 7 minutes with lid on pot. Lower heat and cook 10 minutes. Make sure all of the rice is in stock.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil oleo, brown sugar, dark syrup and cream of tartar together for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda. Mix well and pour over popped corn and put in oven for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir once or twice while cooking.

title: chewy coconut bars(everyone asks for the recipe)
directions: Blend 1/2 cup brown sugar and butter; add 1 cup sifted flour. Pat the mixture on bottom of ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven.

title: quick orange sherbet
directions: Pour
all ingredients into freezer container and freeze until firm.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry.
Blend eggs slightly.
Beat in remaining ingredients. Pour egg mixture into pie pan.
Cook, uncovered, at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 300° and cook until knife inserted in center comes out clean (about 30 minutes).
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: scotch-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, butterscotch chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on a cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: george washington pudding
directions: Combine the fruit and 1 cup of sugar; let stand while preparing the batter.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: garden vegetables
directions: Place frozen mixed vegetables in a Dutch oven.
Steam only until vegetables are crisp.
Toss with Golden Caesar dressing to coat.
Reheat quickly to preserve the crispness of the vegetables.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Stir brown sugar into oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a deep square pan for approximately 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares. Can then be dipped in powdered sugar for a variation.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together into a loaf and bake, uncovered, at 350° in an 11 x 7-inch dish for 1 hour or until loaf is done in center.
Serves 6.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together in large bowl.
Set to one side.
Brown hamburger meat in skillet.
Grease large skillet and brown a small amount of corn meal in bottom.
Place
a layer of first mixture in skillet, then place hamburger meat on top of this.
Add cheese, onion and peppers.
Place the rest of the corn bread mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peach crispy
directions: Slice enough peaches to cover the bottom of a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and
egg with fork.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Over crumbs, pour melted
butter.
Sprinkle
with cinnamon.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Can also be made using apples.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Flour and roll to fit a small cookie sheet one sheet of puff pastry.
Prick with fork before baking; bake according to directions.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Spread mixture on cooled pastry.
Top with fresh peach slices, strawberries, blueberries, etc.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Cover first 3 ingredients with water and pickling salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain in the morning.
Mix sugar and vinegar, don't heat.
Stir until dissolved. Pour over cucumbers. Put in freezer container and freeze.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut crusts off bread.
Cut bread slices into 4 fingers.
Toast crust and bread fingers at 200° for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Roll crusts into a fine crumb.
Mix together peanut butter and oil in saucepan over low heat, stirring well.
Dip bread sticks into peanut butter mixture and roll in crumbs.
Place on wax paper.
Nice for a party or to serve as a snack; isn't very sweet.

title: new orleans shrimp spices for boiling shrimp
directions: Add crab boil to water and bring to a boil.
When rolling, add shrimp.
Boil 1 minute.
Turn off heat and let shrimp stand in water 10 minutes.
Remove shrimp.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In a skillet brown meat, peppers and onions. Drain.
Reduce heat and add rice and tomatoes.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour in casserole dish and add Fritos and top with grated cheese.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Fry meat in oil.
Add mushrooms, green onion, rice and soy sauce.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Dribble egg over rice and cook for 5 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Cut chicken into cubes.
Add egg white, 1 tablespoon of soy sauce and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Marinate for 1/2 hour.
Deep fry and set aside.

title: hot mustard
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar in a small pan and let stand overnight.
Next day, stir in sugar.
Add eggs and salt.
Cook until thickened.
This is very hot; use sparingly.
Good on any kind of meat sandwiches.

title: polka-dot dessert
directions: Place pudding mix in a large mixing bowl.
Add milk.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Fold softened ice cream into pudding mixture.
Turn into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top.
Freeze.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 9.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Dice or place in blender, peppers, onions and garlic.
Add to other ingredients and simmer 3 hours.
Put in jars and seal. Makes about 16 pints.

title: toll house oatrage snack cake
directions: Combine butter, oats, flour,
brown
sugar,
nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Beat for 3 minutes
at
medium
speed
of mixer. Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread
batter
in	8 x 8-inch microwavable square dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High power for 4 minutes; rotate 1/4 turn.	Cook on High for 4 to 5 minutes longer until top of
cake
appears dry and bottom of cake
is an even color.
Sprinkle
with
1	cup
chocolate chips. Let stand for 10
minutes;	then
spread
chips evenly over top of cake.
Cut into serving pieces.
Enjoy!

title: easy homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: In large bowl, stir together sweetened condensed milk and syrup.
Fold in whipping cream.
Pour into aluminum foil-lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Cover.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into ball.
Let cool about 1 hour, or until firm enough to be rolled in chopped nuts.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in each crust.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans in each.
Top with pie filling, then Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Makes 2.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mash beans; add remaining ingredients, except bacon.
Heat over low flame.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Makes 2 cups dip.

title: chicken broccoli stir-fry
directions: Combine 3/4 cup water, 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 2 tablespoons soy sauce; set aside.
Combine remaining cornstarch and soy sauce; stir it into chicken pieces until well-coated.

title: vegetable pilaf
directions: Brown rice and crumbled fideo in oil.
Add vegetables and broth.
Cover and cook over medium heat until liquid is absorbed (about 20 minutes).
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: butterscotch lollipops
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and water in saucepan.
Place over medium heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to hard-crack stage without stirring.
Wipe crystals from sides of pan frequently or put lid on until crystals are dissolved.
Remove from heat and add butter, salt and coloring.
Stir only until dissolved and mixed.
Drop from teaspoon onto well-buttered flat surface.
Insert skewers.
Makes 8 to 10 lollipops.

title: miss ruby's barbecue sauce
directions: Cook pork (3 or 4 Boston butts, approximately 3 to 4 pounds or 2 large pork shoulders) until it falls off the bone.
Cut up pork with scissors.
Add sauce.
Cook in medium oven for an hour, turning once until brown on each side.
(I've tried to clean this up a bit since it goes back generations in my family and begins "dig a hole to bury and cook the pig, in the backyard...")

title: yeast loaf bread
directions: Scald milk (heat until skim forms on top; do not boil).
Cool to lukewarm.
Put 1/2 cup of the milk in small bowl and dissolve yeast in it.
Pour remaining milk over sugar, salt and Crisco and stir to dissolve.
Add yeast and milk mixture and stir.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour and beat until bubbly.
Continue adding flour until dough will not stick to sides of bowl.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in an airtight container.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil a whole chicken and use the broth, (optional:
chicken can be added to recipe) Mix all ingredients together, place into dish and bake for 45 min. at 425 degrees.

title: basic amish pie shell
directions: Blend and work in 3 or 4 tablespoons water.
Roll; place in pan.
Prick with fork; refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine meat, bread crumbs, egg, onion and seasonings.
Work mixture with hands until blended.
On a sheet of waxed paper, shape mixture into a 6 x 14-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle with chopped sauerkraut and grated cheese, leaving a 1-inch border around all edges.
Starting with narrow end, roll mixture jelly roll fashion.
Seal edges.
Place in a shallow baking dish and bake for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: steaks in foil
directions: Season steaks and lay on foil.
Put onion, bell pepper, garlic and mushrooms on top of steaks, wrap with foil.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook until done in oven (1/2 hour).
Serve with baked potato and salad.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 c. hot water.
Add 3/4 cup cold water, pineapple, cheese, nuts and marshmallows.
When almost jelled, fold in whipped cream.

title: corkie's granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Mix liquid, then sprinkle through dry ingredients and mix well.
Spread on cookie sheets and bake at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir once or twice, baking until dry and golden.

title: auntie's fudge
directions: Cook ingredients together, without stirring, until a soft ball forms when dropped in water.
Cool and beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts, if desired.
Pour onto buttered dish and cut into squares when cooled.

title: honey nut granola
directions: Combine all ingredients, except raisins; mix well.
Bake in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 325°, stirring occasionally.
Stir in raisins.
Spread mixture onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Store in airtight container in a cool, dry place, or in refrigerator.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: oreo cheese cake
directions: Mix and press in pan.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes at 350°.

title: mystery casserole
directions: Brown beef; add tomatoes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
In casserole dish, place in layer. Cover with meat mixture and top with a layer of sliced potatoes. Cover and cook for about 1 hour at 350°.
The last 10 minutes, sprinkle cheese on top and leave it in the oven until bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Debone; cut in pieces. Mix sour cream and soup.
Add chicken.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown cracker crumbs in oleo.
Spread over chicken. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: herb bread
directions: Melt butter in a glass loaf pan.
Sprinkle sesame seed, onion salt, and parsley flakes into melted butter.
Dip individual biscuits into butter and herbs.
Stand on end in dish.
Make 2 rows in loaf dish.
Sprinkle additional sesame seed on top and bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until center is done.

title: sara's favorite chicken wings
directions: Split wings at joint and discard tips.
In a large bowl mix remaining ingredients.
Add chicken wings, turn to coat.
Allow to marinate for at least 1 hour, up to 24 hours, in the refrigerator. Place on a baking pan and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce puffs
directions: Mix together sugar, egg, applesauce and milk. Add cinnamon and Bisquick. Mix thoroughly. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Just mix all ingredients together.
Marinate chicken with it. Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Stir occasionally.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add mashed bananas, salt, beaten eggs, flour, nuts, and vanilla.
Combine water with baking soda and add last to the ingredients above.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.

title: semi-hot dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave dish.
Add can of mushroom soup and stir until blended.
Add 1 can diced hot or semi-hot peppers.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, broth and water in saucepan.
Simmer, covered, 35 minutes.
Pour into blender.
Cover.
Blend until smooth.
Return to boiling.
Stir in milk, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 4 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Garnish with chives, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into greased and floured stem pan. Bake 50 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together first 9 ingredients into balls.
Put in deep, flat baking pan.

title: louella's vegetable pizza
directions: *Such as broccoli, cauliflower, onions, lettuce, peppers, tomatoes, carrots, finely chopped, or black olives.

title: easy baked barbecue pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops on baking dish; place in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until light brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in a double boiler and cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix until butter has melted.
Spoon into cooked pie shell.
Add meringue, if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place into a prepared pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for approximately 30 minutes (or until knife placed in center comes out clean).

title: lillian's meatless lasagna
directions: Cook and drain pasta and lay flat on foil to cool.
Combine Ricotta and Parmesan with eggs, salt and pepper.
Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, cover with pasta, overlapping edges slightly.
Spread 1/2 Ricotta cheese filling over pasta, top with a layer of pasta, repeat.
Cover with pasta, remaining sauce and shredded Mozzarella.

title: bundt pan blueberry cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together (baking powder and flour). Reserve 1 cup of this mixture.
Add remaining flour to batter mixture and beat well.
Dredge blueberries in reserved flour mixture; fold this into batter.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle top with a little sugar.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: louisiana beans and rice
directions: Fry rice in hot oil until rice is a golden color.
Saute pepper, celery, onion and garlic powder in margarine. Stir into rice. Add chicken broth, salt, bay leaf and beans.
Put a piece of wax paper on top, then cover with a lid.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 45 minutes. Fluff before serving.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple until boiling.
Add jello.
Let set until cool and partially jelled.
Fold in buttermilk and Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: texas banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in bowl.
Add egg and bananas; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Fold in nuts.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple and cheddar gratin
directions: In a well-buttered 1-quart shallow baking dish, arrange apple slices and sprinkle with raisins, cinnamon and lemon juice.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Blend in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal, then add cheese and toss.
Sprinkle mixture over apples and bake in upper third of oven, preheated at 350,° for 30 minutes or
until apples are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: overnight salad
directions: Pack down.
After packing place Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.
Top with sliced tomatoes to garnish.

title: chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat flour tortillas in microwave wrapped in paper towel.
Put chicken breasts and grated cheese in tortillas.
Mix soups and milk and pour over top of enchiladas.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with more cheese on top and serve with sour cream.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add taco seasoning per instructions on package.
Drain pinto beans and heat in microwave, about 5 minutes on Medium.
Mash beans and blend in cheese soup.
Mix in completed taco meat. Top with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tea ring in bundt pan
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Pour in Bundt pan.
Mix next three ingredients in a bowl.
Take buttermilk biscuits and roll in 2nd ingredients, then place in pan on their sides.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When done, take and dump them upside-down on a plate and serve hot.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Dough will be very stiff.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Let cool on rack.
Store in airtight container. Makes 8 dozen.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix with strawberries and rhubarb and pour into pastry lined pie plate.
Top with second half of pastry, either solid or lattice.
Seal to bottom crust and flute. Cut slits in center if solid top.
Bake at 425° for 55 minutes.

title: quick pickled beets
directions: Drain juice from beets.
Add remaining ingredients to juice and bring to boiling.
Pour over beets and set in refrigerator to chill and season overnight.

title: persian potato salad
directions: Dice, boil and drain the potatoes.
Drain peas.
Debone and dice the chicken.
Mix all ingredients together, saving 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Form into an oblong shape on a meat platter.
Spread leftover mayonnaise on top.
Decorate with olives and tomatoes. Serves 12.

title: banana delight cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add shortening, buttermilk and bananas.
Mix until dry ingredients are dampened, then beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 1 minute longer.
Dredge nuts in flour and fold in by hand.

title: praline sweet potatoes
directions: Mash hot potatoes.
Stir in sugar, butter, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Put in 3-quart baking dish.
Spread topping over potatoes and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Then add tomato sauce.
Season, then let it simmer.
Boil noodles as directed on box.
Drain noodles.
Layer in a casserole dish the noodles, then meat sauce, then 1 layer of each cheese.
Continue until ingredients run out. Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes, then uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant until tender; drain and mash.
Add all ingredients except topping.
Sprinkle top with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain. Combine cream of mushroom soup, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and diced onion.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Cook Tater Tots and drain.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cracker crumbs.
Reserve rest.

title: tasty party punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in 1 cup boiling water in 1-gallon container.
Add fruit juices.
Fill container with water, mixing well.
Freeze until firm.
Thaw slightly and add ginger ale to serve.
Yields 20 servings.

title: spicy drumsticks
directions: You will also need 1 Reynolds cooking bag.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Combine eggs, corn meal, corn, milk and oil.
Pour half of the mixture into a 2-quart baking dish.
Spread sausage and cheese, then pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: swedish slaw
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar to boiling point.
Don't boil! Pour over cabbage and toss.

title: baked fillet of fish(low in calories, tastes great and is easy)
directions: Place the slices of lemon side by side in the bottom of a baking dish.
Put fillets on top of the lemon slices.
Sprinkle in the sequence listed all the remaining ingredients.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes or until flesh is no longer translucent and flakes readily.
Serves 4.

title: crescent roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, mushrooms and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on uncooked rolls.
Roll up and bake until golden brown.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Toss lightly and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12 x 3-inch loaf pan or 2-quart casserole dish. In a large mixing bowl, combine chicken, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Pour into bottom of pan.
In a small bowl, combine soup and milk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine stuffing mix, water and margarine.
Spoon over mixture in pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo and 1/2 cup nuts; put in 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes; let cool.
Cream the cream cheese with 10x sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Mix and put over second layer.
Mix vanilla instant pudding and chocolate instant pudding with the milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour over second layer.
Spread with Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: pork barbecue for buns
directions: To chopped vegetables, add mustard, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Put spices in a cloth bag tightly tied, so that spices will not spill out.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add the cooked roast pork, cut fine, and catsup.
Allow to simmer a while. Can be made ahead and reheated over low heat.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and/or zucchini and onion 5 to 10 minutes until crisp-tender.
Drain mixture well.
In large bowl, combine soup and sour cream; stir in carrot.
Fold in zucchini/squash and onion.
Toss stuffing mix with butter.
Spread 1/2 stuffing mixture in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon zucchini mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture over it. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through or in microwave uncovered on High 7 minutes, giving dish 1/2 turn after 4 minutes.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add chopped pecans.
Bake at 375° for 8 - 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and peanut butter.
Add egg; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Form into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press flat with small fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Pour berries into buttered 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan (or 8 x 8-inch square pan).
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Stir together flour, sugar and egg until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Spread over berries.
Drizzle melted margarine over topping.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: dorito pie
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain. Layer chips, meat and onions, beans, cheese, mushroom soup/rotel mixture. Bake at 350° for 30- 40 minutes.

title: applesauce fruitcake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually with spices, creaming until light.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Dredge fruit and nuts in 1/2 cup of the flour.
Beat eggs until light.
Add butter mixture.
Mix flour mixture in; stir until well blended.
Put in fruit, nuts and applesauce.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hearty beef 'n potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and up sides of 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef in large chunks; drain.
Place beef, broccoli, 1/2 can French fried onions and tomatoes in potato shells.
Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings; pour over beef mixture.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, Tabasco sauce, celery and mustard seed in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Combine with remaining ingredients; chill. Yields 1 2/3 cups.

title: crabbies
directions: Melt cheese and butter together and mix with other ingredients. Spread on halves of English muffins.
Cut each muffin into 6 pieces (pie shaped).
Put on cookie sheet to freeze, then put in plastic Ziploc bag to store in freezer.
When ready to serve, thaw and bake at 400° for 12 minutes or broil for 2 minutes until bubbly.

title: caruso hash
directions: Slice and fry onion. Add the crumbled hamburger meat and brown well. Add the rice and stir a bit to let brown a little. Add the tomatoes and seasonings. Cover and cook about 30 minutes. Serve piping hot. Serves about 6. Can freeze. Can make ahead.

title: extra easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce; heat through. In a large baking dish, spread 1 1/2 cups meat mixture.
Top with 3 uncooked noodles, half of the Ricotta cheese and half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Slowly pour water around inside edges of baking dish. Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Stir in the cranberry sauce until it melts.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Let jell.

title: old-fashioned ham and bean soup
directions: Place beans in water in a large pot; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Add ham bone, onion, celery, carrots and all spices.
Simmer for 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Remove ham bone and cut meat; return to soup.
Remove bay leaf.
Garnish with hard-cooked egg yolk slices.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: reese cups
directions: Melt margarine and mix all ingredients together. If very dry, add more peanut butter.

title: ham and shrimp casserole
directions: Bring water to boil, add beef cubes and bay leaf.
When cubes are dissolved, add rice and cook until done.
Remove bay leaf. Brown onion and pepper in butter.
Combine these with rice and remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole. Cover with crumbled potato chips or buttered bread crumbs and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry squares(great for diabetics)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add all ingredients except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of jello mixture into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Let gel in refrigerator.
Spread sour cream on gelled mixture.
Pour remaining mixture over sour cream and return to refrigerator and completely set.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: After soaking bread crumbs in milk, add onion, meat, egg and seasonings.
Mix; shape into 1-inch balls.
Saute in margarine or butter until light brown on all sides.
Remove meatballs from pan; set aside.
Melt margarine or butter in same pan.
Add flour, bouillon cube mixture, milk and sour cream.
Cook these ingredients, stirring constantly until thick.
Add meatballs to mixture and simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: canned hot packed peaches
directions: This is the best way to can peaches!

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: cornflake treats
directions: Boil corn syrup and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Remove from stove.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Add cornflakes.
Mix until all cornflakes are coated with mixture.
Drop from teaspoon on waxed paper.
Allow to cool.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: daughter-in-law nova's christmas quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Make sure it doesn't jiggle.
May be topped with canned onion rings during last 10 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together, serve and be ready for everyone asking, "What is this?
It's good!"

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred
cabbage	into
a
large	casserole dish (not too fine), add
salt
and
pepper.
Mix
tomato
and mushroom soup thoroughly and
pour	over
cabbage.	Add sliced onions, then spread ground beef
over all (make sure ground beef is spread smoothly over all of the other ingredients).	Casserole should be 3/4 full.
Cover with heavy foil and seal tightly.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Squeeze juice from oranges.
Grate rind of 1/2 orange.
Mix together with sugar and let set while making jello.
Mix red jello and boiling water; mix with cranberry mixture.
Mix in crushed pineapple with juice and grated apples. Place in refrigerator to set.

title: quick and easy mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, then add diced onion. Add seasoning mix, chili and diced tomatoes and onions to the beef mixture. Put layer of 10-inch tortillas in a 9 x 8-inch pan. Top with a layer of meat mixture, a layer of cheese, a layer of tortillas, a layer of meat mixture and a layer of cheese. Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix liquid ingredients with egg beater. Pour liquid ingredients into sifted dry ingredients quickly.
Bake in hot pans (greased thoroughly) in a hot 425° oven.

title: sweet onion casserole
directions: Cook rice in 5 cups boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain; set aside.
Cook onions in butter in large skillet until limp but not browned.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, then add pineapple, apple, nuts and cranberry sauce. Mix well, then turn into 9 x 13 pan. Refrigerate.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° until done.

title: london chicken
directions: Brown the chicken in butter. Then brown mushrooms if using fresh ones. Place chicken in a large casserole. Mix the soups (undiluted) and pour over chicken. Place mushrooms on top. Refrigerate. When ready to bake, add wine, cover the casserole, and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Makes 12 servings.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Roll graham crackers with rolling pin until very fine.
Melt marshmallows and milk in a double boiler.
Mix all other ingredients and pour melted marshmallows and milk over them.
Mix well and pack in the cracker box and put in icebox 24 hours before cutting.

title: chocolate divinity
directions: Lightly oil inside of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Combine water and corn syrup in pan.
Cook over moderate heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add sugars, chocolate and nutmeg.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until sugars are completely dissolved and chocolate is melted.
Wipe down sugar crystals above liquid line, using clean pastry brush dipped in cold water.
Cook without stirring, until mixture boils.
Wipe down sugar crystals.
Clip on candy thermometer.
Cook over moderate heat of 260° (hard ball stage).

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, building up slightly around the edges.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: breakfast of champions
directions: Place sourdough bread, cut in cubes, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook sausage just until it changes color and arrange over bread.
Then add cheese, salt and pepper over mixture in pan.
Do not stir.

title: real italian lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef in a skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.

Add the onions, tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings. Simmer for 30 minutes or longer, adding water gradually as needed. Layer the lasagna noodles, sauce, cottage cheese, Cheddar, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses 1/2 at a time in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Mix together sugar, cider vinegar, salt and pepper. Add vegetable oil and shake to mix well.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Add sugar to butter.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in oats and coconut.
Shape into balls.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or less.

title: ice cream
directions: You will need 1 pint size zip-type plastic bag and 1 gallon size zip-type plastic bag.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: For a 5 to 7 pound brisket.
Place meat on large sheet of aluminum foil.
Pour liquid smoke over brisket.
Sprinkle on celery salt, onion salt and garlic salt.
(Rub into meat on both sides.)
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together. Chill. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: black forest cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 3 layers.
Cool as directed.
Place 1st layer down.
Put a few drops of rum flavoring on top.
Spread some cherry pie filling.
Top with whipped cream.
Repeat with other layers.
Place in freezer for about 30 minutes, or until whipped cream is firm.

title: pork tenderloin with chutney
directions: Cut meat into eight equal size pieces.
Put butter in skillet on medium-high and brown pork.
Put pork in shallow baking pan. Put whipping cream in skillet and scrape up brown bits.
Stir in chutney.
Mix well.
Pour over pork.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Put popcorn in a greased 15 1/2 x 10-inch pan.
Melt butter, sugar and corn syrup together (bring to a boil).
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, salt and soda.
Pour syrup over popcorn.
Add nuts, if you want. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and fruit cocktail.
Let gel, stir, then add other ingredients.
Stir again and let gel.

title: apricot lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
As soon as cake is done take a table knife and poke holes all over cake.
Spread glaze slowly over cake while cake is hot.

title: golden puffs
directions: Heat 3 to 4-inches oil to 375°.
Measure flour, 1/4 cup sugar and nutmeg into bowl.
Add oil, milk and egg; beat until smooth. Drop by teaspoons (too large puffs will not cook) into fat.
Fry 4 or 5 at a time, about 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain. Sift together 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Roll warm puffs in sugar-cinnamon mixture.

title: dreamy banana salad
directions: Whip cream.
Put a layer of wafers in bottom of a large dish. Add a layer of pineapple with juice.
Layer of bananas and layer of whip cream.
Repeat until ingredients are gone.

title: corn cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain whole kernel corn; spread in casserole dish.
Add cream-style corn and Cheez Whiz.
Bake 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add yolks, milk and vanilla. Cook over low heat until thick.
Beat in butter.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) baked or graham cracker shells.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Spread over pie and brown.

title: hot cheese and crab dip
directions: Cut cheeses in small pieces.
Combine over low heat until cheeses melt.
Stir in wine and crab; heat through.
Serve in chafing dish with Shredded Wheat wafers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Wrap sausage around hard-boiled eggs, covering completely. Coat with beaten eggs and roll in crumbs.
Deep fry in oil for 8 minutes or until sausage is done.

title: cheese salad
directions: Dissolve pimento cheese in hot water.
Add
package
of lemon jello and crushed pineapple.
Let set
until mushy.
Add 1 carton Cool Whip.	Let set overnight or until firm.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream together the brown sugar, butter or margarine, eggs, bourbon or orange juice and milk.
Sift together the cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg, cloves, soda and flour.
Mix flour mixture with fruit, nuts and raisins, then mix with liquids.
Bake in a 275° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, whipped topping and egg.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar; roll to coat.
Place balls 1 1/2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from sheet.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: individual pizzas
directions: Give each child 1/2 of English muffin.
Spoon sauce over muffin.
Top with grated cheese and broil or bake until cheese is melted.

title: white almond bark candy
directions: Heat bark in microwave according to directions.
Mix in nuts, marshmallows and Cocoa Puffs into white bark.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Let candy set until hard.
Store in airtight container.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix this all together.
Put in refrigerator until chilled. Take out and make small balls; cool again.
Put in a double boiler 3 tablespoons vegetable oil and 1 package of peanut butter chips or any other chip you like.
Let this all melt; stir until smooth. Dip each ball into mixture; put on wax paper and chill.

title: cauliflower or broccoli soup
directions: Cook cauliflower.
Mash 1/3.
Chop rest of cauliflower.
Cook chopped onion and chopped celery in 1/4 cup butter.
Add flour and cook briefly.
Add chicken broth, water and bouillon; cook until thickened.
Add cauliflower, grated cheese and milk.
Heat through and serve.

title: taco pies
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and 1 cup water.
Simmer until done.
Place separated biscuit layers in greased cupcake pans.
Press in bottom and on sides.
Fill with taco meat; top with cheese and bake at 350° until dough is golden brown and cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: oreo brownies
directions: Combine Oreo crumbs and butter.
Press firmly into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
In a medium saucepan, melt 1 cup chips with milk and vanilla over medium heat.
Pour evenly over prepared crust.
Sprinkle with remaining chips.
Bake for 20 minutes or until set at 350°.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have all ingredients at about 75°. Sift flour before measuring.
Measure flour and add baking powder and salt to it.
In a separate bowl, blend until creamy the shortening, sugar and lemon rind.
Beat into this mixture 1 to 2 beaten eggs and 1 to 1 1/4 cups ripe banana pulp.
Add the sifted ingredients in about 3 parts to the sugar mixture.
Beat the batter after each addition until smooth.
Fold in optional ingredients now, if desired.
Place batter in a greased bread pan. Bake the bread for about 1 hour or until done.
Cool before slicing.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 2 hours. Hollow out round bread, saving excess bread for dipping.
Fill round bread with mixture.
Cut excess bread into cubes for dipping into spinach dip.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook amount of noodles desired in water with 1 tablespoon of oil and 1/2 teaspoon salt until chewy, but tender.
Drain. Do not rinse off.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, water, vanilla, oats, flour, salt and soda.
Mix well on low speed of mixer.
Add raisins; blend evenly.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes; let cool.

title: tuna gumbo salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water. Add rest of ingredients.
Set in mold sprayed with Pam.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into Pyrex baking dish. Crush the Ritz crackers and pour over top.
Melt oleo and pour over top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy sweet dills
directions: Drain juice off of pickles.
Combine garlic, vinegar, spices and sugar.
Bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Add pickles and bring to a boil again.
Remove from heat.
Pack and cover with syrup.
Leave 1/4 inch at top.
Process 5 minutes in hot bath. Yields 2 quarts.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, nuts, bananas, flour and soda.
Bake in greased loaf pans for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°. Makes 2 loaves.

title: poppy seed salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine lettuce and onions.
Refrigerate. In small skillet, saute the almonds with 1 tablespoon sugar and butter; set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine oil, vinegar, 1/4 cup sugar and seasonings.
Mix well.
Just before serving, add noodles, almonds and dressing to lettuce.
Mix well.

title: holly potatoes
directions: Melt butter.
Mix flour, cheese, seasoning and paprika.
Scrub potatoes and dry.
Cut into quarters.
Dip each piece in butter and then in mixture.
Lay on pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb charlotte
directions: Use brown and white sugars to sweeten rhubarb.
Put stewed rhubarb in ovenproof dish.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk. Pour resulting batter over fruit.
Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut squares
directions: Microwave 3/4 cup (1 1/2 sticks) margarine and 2 squares chocolate on High 1 to 2 minutes or until melted when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in crumbs, coconut and peanuts. Press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Chill 30 minutes. Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Spread over crust.
Chill 30 minutes.
Microwave remaining margarine and chocolate squares on High 1 to 2 minutes or until melted when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill.
Cut into about 4 dozen squares, small squares.

title: lynette's franklin nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add 3 cups flour which has been sifted with baking powder and salt.
Mix 1 cup of flour with fruit and nuts; add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 250° (225°) for 3 hours.
Let cool in pan.

title: coconut macaroon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a cookie sheet well.
Mix flour, coconut and salt together in a bowl.
Pour in condensed milk and vanilla.
Stir well to
make thick batter.
Drop batter by quarter cupfuls onto the well-greased cookie sheet, allowing an inch of space between cookies.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 1 1/2 dozen macaroons.

title: hawaiian divinity
directions: Combine sugar, white corn syrup and water.
Boil until mixture spins threads.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add syrup, beating constantly.
When candy thickens, add Hawaiian Punch.
Add chopped nuts.
Beat until stiff.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper. Makes 2 pounds.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together peanut butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add butter and vanilla; blend.
Fold in whipped cream until blended. Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill 4 to 5 hours or until set.
Drizzle top with hot fudge topping.
Chill anywhere from 30 minutes to overnight.

title: light cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan. Remove from oven.
Poke holes in hot cake with end of wooden spoon, about 1-inch apart.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine milk, eggs, spice, salt, sugar and pumpkin.
Pour into an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with Dream Whip.

title: baked shrimp oregano
directions: Put shrimp (1 layer) in a pie plate or baking dish.
Sprinkle lemon juice on top.

title: pizza rice salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Cool.
Toss rice, cheese, pepperoni, tomato, green pepper, mushrooms, olives and 1/4 cup of the dressing in a large bowl.
Refrigerate.
Toss with remaining 1/2 cup dressing before serving.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix lemon gelatin with hot water.
Set aside.
Mix eggs with cooking oil.
Add cake mix and gelatin mixture.
Pour over cake while still in pan.
Let stand 2 hours.
Remove from pan.

title: burgundy eye round with horseradish spread
directions: Place tablespoon of flour in oven bag and shake to coat sides. Season meat with seasoned salt, garlic and pepper (season to your liking).
Place roast into oven bag and pour wine over roast.
Tie off bag.
Place bag into baking pan and refrigerate to marinate overnight.
When ready to bake, place slits into bag, about 6, then insert meat thermometer.
Bake at 325° until thermometer reads 140°, about 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and slice thin.

title: betty's baked corn
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, salt and pepper.
Mix and add sugar and flour.
Add creamed corn and melted butter.
Place in 8 x 11 pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: split pea soup
directions: Soak peas in water in a large kettle.
Bring to boil gently for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour. Add ham, onion and parsley.
Heat to boil; cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours, until peas are tender and liquid is partially cooked down.
Season to taste with pepper and salt.
For a smooth soup, put through a sieve.
Dilute as desired with additional milk or water.

title: end of garden pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, pepper, cabbage, onion and tomatoes in salt water overnight (1/2 cup salt to 2 quarts water).
Cook beans and carrots until tender; drain water off.
Add soaked vegetables and cooked vegetables together with other ingredients; boil 10 minutes.
Can while hot.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown
pork chops (salt, pepper and flour first) in 1/2 stick of
butter.
Grease
the casserole dish
with
butter. Sprinkle garlic salt in butter.
Now lay pork
chops
in dish. Put
a slice of onion, bell pepper and tomato
on
each
pork chop. Sprinkle 3/4 cup of rice around dish, then add a can of beef consomme soup and 1 can of water and then
cover and cook at 300° for an hour.
Uncover dish 10 minutes
before
done so moisture will cook down.

title: oyster cocktail sauce
directions: In a saucepan, thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until ready to serve.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Combine 1/4 cup of the barbecue sauce, 1/4 cup water and the egg in a large bowl. Stir in bread crumbs, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Mix in meat until well combined. On a baking pan, shape the meat mixture into a loaf. Bake 1 hour. Spread remaining 1/4 cup sauce over top and sides of meat loaf and continue baking 30 minutes longer. Let stand 10 minutes before slicing. Makes 12 slices.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 to 30 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; let cool completely on a wire rack.

title: m & m cookies
directions: Mix all together and put on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Take out of oven and decorate.

title: heavenly chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine candy bars and condensed milk in a large saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until candy bars melt. Cool, stirring occasionally.
Add one quart milk to candy mixture. Beat until well blended.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a gallon ice cream freezer.
Stir in chocolate syrup and add enough milk to fill container 4 inches from top.
Freeze according to directions of manufacturers.

title: chicken and sausage
directions: Put oil in skillet; add sausage and chicken.
Cook over medium heat adding 1/2 cup water at a time to keep from sticking.
When chicken is 3/4 done, add onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until onion is done.
Add enough water to make gravy.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Mix with hand beater until lumps are gone.
Spray small frypan with
Pam.
Put
large tablespoons at a time in hot pan. Brown
for
a
few
seconds on each side.
Place cottage cheese mixed
with
a little sour cream into center and roll. Serve with strawberry preserves and sausage.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Lightly toast coconut and pecans in oven until coconut is slightly brown. Pour mixture into crust and drizzle with caramel. Top with pecans and coconut. Chill for 2 hours.

title: bacon and egg casserole souffle
directions: Butter an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Layer stuffing croutons and Cheddar cheese.
Combine eggs, salt, pepper, onion salt and milk; mix until well blended.
Pour over croutons and cheese.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Break into bite size pieces and lay on top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve immediately. Serves 8.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Beat eggs. Add Eagle Brand, water and vanilla.
Add cookies and cream. Blend.
Pour into cake pan and place in freezer for 4 to 6 hours.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix well.
Use 1/4 cup to 1 cup water.

title: wilma's sponge cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In small bowl, beat eggs yolks until very thick.
Pour yolks into large mixer bowl.
Gradually beat in sugar. On low speed, mix in flour, baking powder and salt alternately with water, flavorings and lemon peel.
In another bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Gradually fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes.
Invert pan on funnel.
Let hang until cake is completely cool.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the poppy seed, in a bowl. Beat with a mixer for 4 minutes.
Add poppy seed and stir in with a spoon.
Spray bread pans with Pam.
Pour batter into 2 regular or 4 small bread pans.
Do not fill more than halfway (you will have a little left over).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until when a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: brunch fruit
directions: Empty all fruits and juices into large bowl.
Add fresh fruits and pudding mix (dry from box).
Stir and mix well.
Let set several hours.

title: oriental rice
directions: Preheat a large skillet over high heat.
Add oil and scramble eggs.
Add cooked rice and vegetables.
Stir and toss to blend quickly.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Mix with diced chicken and remaining ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: french toast bundles
directions: Cut bread into 3/4-inch slices.
Put a slice of cheese and a slice of bacon between the bread.
Dip the bundles in the egg on both sides.
Spray pan with Pam and heat over medium heat until hot.
After Pam is hot, add bundles and cook for 2 1/2 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn bundles and cook another 1 1/2 minutes or until golden brown.
Spread strawberry preserves on top or sift powdered sugar on top.

title: lite spinach-bacon deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Scoop out yolks into a small mixing bowl and mash with fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon yolk mixture into white halves.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: crepes
directions: In a bowl mix flour, sugar and salt together.
Dig a little hole and put the eggs and the oil in it.
Stir all the ingredients, then add the milk, little by little, until you get a liquid but smooth dough.
Let this dough set in a cool place for an hour.

title: chinese chews(date cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift dry ingredients; add to nuts and dates.
Mix and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes (one 9 x 12-inch pan and one 9 x 9-inch pan).
Place pans on wet towel to cool.
Cut into small squares.
Roll into balls with greased hands; roll in powdered sugar.

title: fettuccine with minted tomato sauce
directions: Spread walnuts in a shallow pan and toast in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned.
Meanwhile, peel, seed and coarsely chop tomatoes.
If using canned tomatoes, break up with a spoon and use liquid.
In a medium size bowl, combine tomatoes, wine, basil, mint, salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 1 minute, then add sugar, lemon juice, spices, salt and soda.

Mix well, then fold flour and pumpkin in. Spread on greased cookie sheet, then sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Turn out on towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar and roll up with towel.
Let cool.
When cake is
cool, unroll and spread with filling.

title: cheese meltaways
directions: Blend all ingredients and spread on muffin halves.
Cut each into quarters and freeze on a cookie sheet.
Transfer to a plastic bag and keep frozen until ready to use.
Place desired amount on cookie sheet under broiler and cook until cheese is bubbly and brown.
Serve hot.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread on large platter. Spread taco sauce over cheese layer then sprinkle with cheese. Top with green onions and green pepper.
Add chopped tomatoes just before serving.
Serve with warm tortilla chips.

title: cherry cream dessert
directions: Crust:
Combine sugar, crumbs and melted butter; mix thoroughly.
Pack mixture in bottom only of 9 x 6-inch pan.

title: cherry delight
directions: Cream sugar and
cream
cheese until fluffy; set aside. Beat Dream Whip, then
add to cream cheese mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust, top with cherry filling; last add pecans which have been broken
into
pieces.
This
will
keep in the refrigerator for several days.

title: italian chicken soup
directions: Cut each chicken breast half lengthwise in half, then cut halves crosswise into 1/4-inch thick strips.
Chop onion and carrot.
Peel, seed and dice tomatoes.
Trim off ends of green beans; cut each diagonally in half.
Cut yellow squash lengthwise in half, then cut halves crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces.
Prepare macaroni as label directs; drain.

title: cheese crisp
directions: Blend butter and cheese. Cut in remaining ingredients; mix well. Roll into balls and mash with fork. Cook about 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: no cook bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine in a bowl cucumbers, onions, green and red peppers; mix well.
In a saucepan combine vinegar, sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved, pour over cucumber mixture and mix well.
Put in jars, pour leftover juice over cucumbers.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour, then refrigerate.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry garlic and onion in lard until browned.
Add flour, tomato puree, water, chili powder, oregano and cumin.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Beat cake mix, pudding mix, oil and eggs until well blended.
Stir in water and extract.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. When cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: fried trout
directions: Fry in oil at medium heat until fish is tender and slightly browned.

title: les mahaney's stroganoff
directions: Use a slow cooker. One hour before serving, add 1 cup sour cream and mix in. Pour over cooked noodles.

title: glazed spice bars
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until blended.
Press dough into a 9x13 inch cake pan.
Bake at 350°F for 25-30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Drizzle glaze over top.
When glaze dries, cut into squares.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pres into an ungreased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drizzle top of loaf with ketchup; bake 15 minutes more.

title: doughnuts
directions: Roll and cut out. Cook in hot fat.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onions and margarine; then add everything else.

title: "it makes its own crust" easy chicken pie
directions: Simmer chicken until tender.
Cut into bite size pieces. Place in bottom of baking dish, 9 x 12-inch.
Melt butter and mix with broth and soup.
Pour over chicken (may add a small can of peas or carrots).
Mix flour, milk and baking powder.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: wassail
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add orange juice, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Strain out spices and serve warm.

title: roast pheasant
directions: Brown pheasant in butter in Dutch oven or iron skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a small roaster or leave in a Dutch oven.
Add grapes and wine.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until done.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Place onions in skillet.
Add sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Cook 20 minutes, covered.
Add onion mixture to beans. Add crumbled bacon.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer veggies; cover with soup.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 375°.
Uncover; finish baking until done.

title: chewy pecan squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend all ingredients until just moistened. Spread mixture into pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: cream de cacao pie
directions: Soften coffee ice cream slightly.
Pack into pie shell, freeze until firm, at least 1 hour.
At serving time, place a scoop of pistachio on each serving and drizzle 1 to 2 tablespoons creme de cacao.

title: salmon and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Melt butter; blend in flour and add juice drained from salmon, plus enough milk to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir until sauce boils and thickens.
Add salt, pepper and macaroni.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 300°.
Do not open oven until done.

title: ricotta pie(italian easter pie)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pie crust.
Top with crust and bake at 350° to 375° until set.

title: fish pie
directions: Cut cream cheese in small cubes.
Whisk eggs; add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes in a 9 1/2-inch deep dish pie plate.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: ham and egg pie
directions: Place 4 slices of ham in deep baking dish.
Cover with thin crust of biscuit dough.
Cover with broth.
Place 4 slices of ham on dough.
Break eggs and drop around on top of layer.
Cover with top crust and bake in 300° to 350° oven until brown.
Be sure to add plenty of broth.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: In large bowl, mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add sliced bananas; mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust; smooth out.
Layer (drained) crushed pineapple over mixture.
Layer Cool Whip, then coconut, then nuts.
Decorate with cherries. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: snowy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water.
Mash and add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic.
Beat at high speed until smooth.
Stir in chives.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine.
Cool slightly, then sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over pan.
Then sprinkle each of the following over crumbs, one upon the other:
chocolate morsels, butterscotch morsels, coconut, chopped nuts and milk.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: mom's molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and sorghum.
Add egg and buttermilk. Mix well.
Add vinegar and soda mix.
Mix very well.
Add enough of mixture of all dry ingredients to make a soft dough.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each cookie in a crisscross pattern with a fork dipped in cold water.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Extras freeze well.

title: peggy's wine punch
directions: Mix Sauterne, sugar and lemon juice.
Just before serving, add 1 bottle champagne.
Serves 25 to 30 people.

title: wild rice and beef casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Brown ground beef and onion;	drain off grease.
In
large casserole, layer beef, chicken soup, rice, mushroom soup and
cheese.
Bake
at 350° until bubbly.

title: crock-pot chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil and drain.
In slow cooker, combine chicken and remaining ingredients except the spaghetti.
Cook on low for 5 to 7 hours.
Spoon over hot cooked spaghetti.
Makes 5 servings.

title: mincemeat dream bars
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, brown sugar and Crisco.
Press in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.	Spread mincemeat over the crumb crust. Combine:
tablespoons flour, 2 eggs, sugar, instant chocolate, baking
powder,
oatmeal
and coconut.
Blend well. Spread this mixture
over
the mincemeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients to dissolve.
Cut meat into 3/8-inch strips and put in mixture, completely covered.
Marinate for 24 hours.
Take meat out and let drain.
Put in oven across racks; bake at 150° for 6 to 8 hours.
Store in airtight container. Will keep up to 2 years in refrigerator.

title: hannah's frozen fruit ring
directions: Steam large marshmallows and pineapple until melted (double boiler).
Cool and add mayonnaise and whipping cream.
Add rest of ingredients except small marshmallows.
Last, fold in small marshmallows.
Turn into mold and freeze.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Boil sweet potatoes. Mash. Measure 3 cups. Mix with sugar, salt, beaten eggs, butter, milk, cinnamon and vanilla. Spread in a 9-inch square baking dish, sprayed with cooking spray.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Gel.
Add mashed bananas and strawberries, spread a layer on bottom of dish.
Beat Dream Whip.
Add cream cheese and pineapple.
Spread on top of jello.
Cover with another layer of strawberry mixture.
Put in refrigerator until firm.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Melt the 2 sticks margarine, 1/2 cup milk, egg and sugar.
Boil for 1 minute. Add the nuts, coconut and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread this mixture on graham crackers, then place another layer of whole graham crackers and top
with a mixture of the powdered sugar, 1 stick margarine and enough milk for spreading consistency. Refrigerate.

title: spoon bread
directions: Stir corn meal into boiling water for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add butter; beat well.
Add beaten eggs; beat well.
Beat in milk and mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into hot buttered 3-quart Pyrex dish and bake, uncovered, in a preheated 400° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: barbara's fabulous fudge
directions: Mix in a heavy 2-quart saucepan, cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to boil (mixture will be bubbling all over top). Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat.

title: italian style chuck steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim excess fat from steak.
Place in shallow glass baking dish with plenty of space around meat.

title: pecan-topped sweet potatoes
directions: Mash sweet potatoes (you should have about 6 cups).
Beat in eggs, 1/4 cup of the brown sugar, 1/4 cup of the melted butter, salt and cinnamon.
(If the potatoes seem dry, beat in orange juice until moist and fluffy.)
Put in a 2-quart casserole (refrigerate if you wish).
Before baking, arrange pecan halves on top; sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup brown sugar and drizzle with remaining 1/4 cup butter.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate purple ribbon cake
directions: *Or use 1 1/2 cups granulated sugar.

title: hot ziggities
directions: Cut frankfurters in half lengthwise.
Spread cut edges with mustard.
Place back together.
Unroll dough; separate into 8 triangles.
Place frankfurters on wide end of triangle and roll up.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush with barbecue sauce or catsup.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown. Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana pecan waffles
directions: Beat baking mix, bananas, milk, 1/4 cup pecans, oil and egg with wire whisk until blended. Pour batter and cook according to waffle iron instructions. Serve with whipped cream and toasted pecans. Real maple syrup is also delicious with these waffles. Makes 10 servings.

title: jody's fudge
directions: Combine milk with sugar in saucepan.
Heat to boiling and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut.

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Put the whip cream on the graham cracker and top with another cracker.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
Low-fat.

title: fudge upside-down cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and milk; add flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Place in buttered and floured 9 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Toss cabbage and onions.
Toast sunflower seeds and almonds in oven at 250° for 10 minutes.
Mix oil, sugar, vinegar and dry soup mix.
Pour over cabbage mixture just before serving, tossing all together.

title: sugar covered popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn and set aside.
Put water and sugar to boil in a saucepan.
Test mixture in a cup of cold water.
Forms into a ball in cold water, ready to pour over popcorn.
Stir until well coated. Other variations to use with popcorn are raisins, pecans, etc.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Dice all fruit and nuts.
Heat milk and dissolve marshmallows. Crush graham crackers; mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Put in wax lined containers.

title: mexican cabbage
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients together in Dutch oven or a large skillet. Drain off the fat. Add soup. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and tomatoes. Then add cabbage and salt to taste. Simmer slowly for 45 minutes. Use a very large skillet or Dutch oven for this makes a large amount.

title: cheeseburger bake
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add sauce, catsup, flour and salt to taste.
Put in a 9-inch pan and top with cheese.
Place biscuits on top with small space between each.
Bake according to biscuit directions.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook cut ziti noodles for 10 minutes.
Drain.
In a large bowl, combine cooked ziti, 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, oregano and pepper.
In 3-quart casserole, pour 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce. Spread ziti mixture evenly over sauce. Top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until hot.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown beef; season with salt and pepper. Add onion. Drain. Add pizza sauce. Place in 9 x 12 pan. Spread evenly. Arrange pepperoni, mushrooms and green pepper on top of beef mixture. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and add sour cream and Mozzarella cheese. Unroll crescent rolls and lay on top of cheese. Bake at 400° until browned.

title: fudge drop cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together in top of double boiler. Take off heat, stir in milk; blend in flour.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by teaspoonful onto foil lined baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool thoroughly on wire racks.
Makes about 65 cookies.

title: sweet and sour spareribs(serving size: 8)
directions: Combine last 7 ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Add ribs; cover with plastic wrap and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Drain marinade from ribs and discard.
Bake ribs at 375°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: sesame asparagus
directions: Cut rough, hard ends off of asparagus.
Spread asparagus in pan.
Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake in a 500° oven for 10 minutes.

title: pickled beans ala jaussaud's
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain and cover with fresh water.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
Cook at a simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Drain and rinse well.
Combine all other ingredients. Pour over drained beans.
Chill several hours.
Keeps well and improves with time.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill several hours or overnight. Roll thin and cut with small cookie cutter for round crackers or use a pizza cutter and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Prick the center of each one before baking.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in center of oven at 325° for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove to rack or paper towels to cool.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pack in buttered loaf pan.
Place in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn out into platter.
Garnish with hard-boiled eggs.

title: buttermilk fudge squares
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until butter melts and mixture is smooth, remove from heat. Beat buttermilk and next 3 ingredients at medium speed of mixer until smooth. Add butter mixture to buttermilk mixture, beating until blended. Combine sugar, flour, and salt, gradually add to buttermilk mixture, beating until blended. Pour into greased 15 x 10 inch jellyroll pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set. Spread Chocolate Buttermilk Frosting over warm cake.

title: almond gateau
directions: Cream butter, almond paste and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add almond extract and liqueur.
Beat in flour and baking powder only until mixed through.
Do not beat too long.
Pour into a buttered and floured 8-inch round cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes until a knife comes out clean.
When cooled, invert onto platter and dust well with powdered sugar.
Freezes well.
Also keeps for 3 to 4 days.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken vermicelli salad
directions: Break pasta into fourths and cook until done. Chop celery and bell pepper fine.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: eggplant relish
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet.
Add onion and celery and cook until almost tender.
Remove onion and celery and place in a bowl.
In the same skillet, saute eggplant until light brown. Remove.
In same pan over medium flame, place tomato paste and water; stir until dissolved.
Add olives, eggplant, capers, onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil over high flame.
Lower flame; simmer for 5 minutes, then add sugar and vinegar.
Stir and cook for 1/2 minute.
Remove and allow to cool. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: old fashioned cream of tomato soup or 4b's restaurant tomato soup
directions: Mix tomatoes, chicken broth, butter, sugar, onions and soda. Simmer 1 hour.
Heat cream in double boiler (I use microwave). Add cream to hot tomato mixture.
Ready to serve and enjoy.
It's delicious!
This recipe yields 1/2 gallon.

title: sunrise taco
directions: For each taco, spread 1/2 scrambled eggs, 1/4 cup of cheese and 1/4 cup of salsa on tortilla. Roll up. Warm in microwave for about 30 seconds or until cheese melts. Serve immediately.

title: salted chewy bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and 1/3 cup margarine at low speed until crumbly. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 12 to 18 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk, margarine and cinnamon and pour into baking dish.
Pour can of peaches over batter.
Bake at 350°.

title: taco hot dogs
directions: Combine chili sauce and pepper.
Drop frankfurters into boiling water.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 5 to 8 minutes.
Toast buns and put hot dogs in buns.
Spoon chili sauce mixture over hot dogs.
Top with shredded lettuce and cheese.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in a large Dutch oven until tender.
Add chicken broth, pork, chiles, oregano and pepper; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese in a bowl.
Whip together Dream Whip and cold milk in another bowl.
Then blend both together real good.
Spoon into 2 baked pie shells; form outside ring.
Put blueberry pie filling in center.

title: spinach parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain and squeeze excess water.
Combine spinach, cheese, onion, cream, butter, salt and pepper in medium bowl.

title: low-fat chile rellenos casserole
directions: Spray 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray. Sprinkle with chiles and Cheddar cheese.
In medium bowl, combine milk, biscuit mix and eggs, using wire whisk or fork to beat until smooth.
Stir in cottage cheese.
Spoon mixture on top of cheese and chiles.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes until puffed and knife comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Top with salsa, if desired.
A great dish for Sunday brunch. Serves 6.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa and flour; beat the egg yolks, then add the milk.
Cook until it begins to thicken.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Put in oven for about 15 minutes at 450°.

title: lemon angel salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 1/3 cups hot water.
Blend rest of the ingredients into the dissolved jello.
Pour into a 7 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Chill.

title: chocolate carrot cake
directions: Mix together flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and sugars.
Beat together eggs and melted butter with mixer.
Combine mixture with dry ingredients.
By hand, stir in carrots and raisins.
Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) cake pans. Divide batter between pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: chocolate-chunk blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a 9-inch square baking pan.
In a large saucepan, melt the 10 tablespoons butter over low heat and stir in sugar until smooth.
Remove from heat and cool completely. Chop the chocolate.
Combine the flour, baking powder and salt. Beat eggs, one at a time, into the melted butter mixture.
Beat in vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture, then the chocolate chunks. Spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake until edges come away from sides of pan, for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add marshmallows and cheese. Stir well and put in refrigerator to cool and slightly congeal.
Stir well and congeal slightly.
Add rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Return to refrigerator and congeal.

title: tempura veggies
directions: Beat egg yolk. Add butter, salt and 1/4 cup milk.
Add flour and stir until smooth, then add other 1/4 cup milk.
Beat egg white until peaks form.
Add sugar to whites and beat until stiff. Fold into flour mixture.
Dip cut veggies into flour and then into batter.
Deep fry until golden.
Especially good is zucchini, onions, green peppers, mushrooms, broccoli or whatever you like best.
Even apple slices are good this way.
Will do about 2 pounds fresh veggies.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Combine peaches and 3/4 cup sugar in blender or food processor. Process until finely chopped. Set aside. Combine remaining 2 1/4 cups sugar, flour and salt in a Dutch oven. Stir in milk, evaporated milk and eggs. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 10 minutes, until thickened. Cool. Stir in peaches and flavorings. Pour mixture into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: fresh ham
directions: Place the fresh ham on a roasting rack in a Dutch oven on top of the stove.
Combine the ginger ale and white wine together and pour over the ham.
Place in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 2 1/2 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix all together.
Chill.
Use as a dip for gingersnaps or any choice of cookie.
Also, good with pound or angel food cake.

title: blueberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve jello with boiling water.
Add blueberry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan and set until firm.

title: veal and sour cream
directions: Place finely cut onion in cooking oil, frying until light brown.
Stir in paprika.
Cut meat in small pieces and put in skillet; sprinkle with salt.
Cover and let steam, using low setting on stove.
A little water may be added to keep from sticking.
Let cook until tender.
Take sour cream and 1/2 pint of water and flour; mix well with eggbeater.
When meat is tender, pour in the mixture.
Let it come to a boil.
Good served with mashed potatoes.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin as directed on package.
Chill each kind of Jell-O until firm.
Fill the bottom of bowl with 1/2 of both kinds of Jell-O.
Add apples, oranges, bananas, pineapple, coconut and pecans.
Cover with remainder of Jell-O.
Garnish the top with a slice of pineapple in the center and coconut and pecans around the pineapple.
Return to the refrigerator.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet, adding next 5 ingredients.
Cook spaghetti according to directions; drain in hot water.
When hamburger is done, put in big kettle.
Add chili beans (don't drain), tomato soup, tomato juice and chili powder.
Add cooked spaghetti; simmer 15 to 30 minutes.
Top
with shredded cheese.

title: pear preserves(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: To prepare fruit:
Select pears that hold their shape and have a good flavor.
Allow fruit to reach the firm ripe stage.
Wash, pare, core and cut fruit into uniform pieces.

title: spinach enchilada casserole(8 servings)
directions: In large skillet, cook beef with garlic, onion, salt and pepper until beef is crumbled and no longer pink.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, green chiles, lime juice, sugar and spinach.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: stuffed tuscany tenderloin (spinach)
directions: Saute onion in hot oil in a skillet over medium heat until tender. Add spinach, salt and pepper; saute 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in Parmesan cheese and tomatoes.

title: creamed peas and potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil in a large pan for 10 minutes. Add peas and cook until just done.
In a microwavable bowl, melt oleo.
Add flour; stir.
