Cook on High for approximately 2 minutes. Stir in milk.
Cook on High until the mixture thickens, stirring every 1 1/2 minutes.
(Should pull away from the sides and form a rough ball.)
As the potatoes and peas are boiling, add milk thickening, stirring constantly.
You may not need to use all the thickening.

title: pineapple lime mold
directions: Bring 1 cup water to boil; stir in jello until dissolved.
Add remaining 1/2 cup water and juice.
Gradually add jello to cream cheese; mix until blended.
Chill until thickened but not set; fold in pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into 1-quart mold. Chill until firm.
Turn out onto serving plate, surrounded with lettuce.
Serve with assorted fresh fruits.

title: squash bake
directions: Use 1 3/4-quart casserole sprayed with Pam.
Toss vegetables lightly.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 15 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add to the first mixture.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Put into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; sprinkle top with butterscotch bits before baking in a 350° oven for about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Layer coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Makes German chocolate cake mix as directed. Pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and butter. Spread over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg with fork.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.

title: seven-up party salad
directions: Combine Seven-Up and marshmallows in saucepan.
Cook until melted. Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved. Cream the cheese in mixing bowl.
Add hot mixture to cheese and beat until smooth. Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill until almost set. Fold in Cool Whip and mayonnaise.
Pour into oblong dish or mold. Refrigerate until set.

title: perfect baked custard
directions: Soften gelatine in 1/2 cup cold milk.
Heat remaining milk, then add gelatine mixture.
Stir to dissolve.
Beat stiff all the egg whites with 3 tablespoons sugar.
Set aside.
Combine egg yolks, sugar, salt and Tang.
Beat just enough to blend.
Slowly add hot milk mixture.
Mix well.
Pile beaten egg whites on top. Swirl lightly.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan or casserole.
Set into a pan of hot water.
Bake in slow oven, 300°, until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: classic green bean casserole
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 more minutes.

title: naomi's dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and place in jars with dill, garlic and pepper. Heat vinegar, water, salt and alum.
Pour over cucumbers in jars and seal.

title: vegetable cheese bake
directions: In a saucepan, combine vegetables and boiling water.
Bring to a boil again.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain well. Meanwhile, melt the butter in a saucepan.
Blend in flour and cook for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk; simmer, stirring, until smooth and thick.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Mix in vegetables, onion and pimento.
Spread into buttered 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Good served with pork.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in a loaf pan.
When cooled, poke holes in the top and pour the Kahlua over the top.
Allow it sit uncovered overnight.
Break the cake into pieces and put in the bottom of a serving bowl.
Prepare mousse according to package directions.
Layer on top of cake pieces with mousse, Cool Whip and chocolate bars, broken into pieces.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Gradually add flour, mixing until well blended.
Pat into ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-22 minutes or until golden.
Beat eggs, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt until smooth.
Pour over crust and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 40-45 minutes or until set.
Cut into bars.

title: low-fat, no sugar cheesecake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended.
Pour mixture into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry beaten eggs until firm in the oil, remove from heat and mash with fork.
Return eggs to stove with meat.
Add onion.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add rice and mix, then add soy sauce, sugar and salt if needed.
Stir until rice is hot.

title: butterfinger pecan dessert
directions: Cream the egg yolks, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Put all in a mixer and beat. Mix with the batter the whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: giant ginger cookies
directions: Mix together with mixer the shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and molasses and mix on slow speed until blended.
Add flour mixture a little at a time.
The dough will be stiff.

title: cheese and carrot soup
directions: Combine carrots, onion and potatoes with stock in soup pot. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered for 10 minutes. Transfer to blender.
Blend until smooth.
Return to pot.
Stir in buttermilk and nutmeg.
Heat through.
Stir in cheese to melt. Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve garnished with parsley along with whole wheat French bread and green salad.

title: cinnamon pickle rings
directions: Use large cucumbers.
Peel, slice and core out centers for 1 gallon rings.
Place in large pan or gallon glass jar.
Mix pickling lime with enough water to cover.
Let stand 24 hours. Drain.
Wash in clean water.
Soak in cold water for 3 hours.
Mix red food coloring, powdered alum and enough water to cover cucumbers in large kettle.
Simmer 2 hours.
Drain.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, sugar, 1 cup water, cinnamon sticks and red hots. Pour over cucumbers.
Reheat syrup for 3 days and pour over cucumbers.
After 3 days, pack cucumbers into hot jar and pour hot syrup over them.
Seal.

title: fruit and pasta salad
directions: Finely shred enough orange peel to make 1/2 teaspoon; set aside.
Remove the remaining peel from orange and section orange over a bowl to catch juice.
Measure 2 tablespoons of the juice.

title: tuna cheese bake
directions: Mix macaroni shells and cheese as directed on box.
Add tuna, cream of mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle with either Durkee French fried onions or crumbled Ruffles potato chips.
Preheat oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can use 2 cans of tuna, if desired.

title: baked french toast
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 pan. Slice bread in 1 1/2-inch slices. Place all in pan overlapping. Mix all the ingredients in a bowl. Pour over bread. Cover. Refrigerate overnight.

title: casserole-barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken breast halves between sheets of wax paper or plastic wrap.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: ham loaf
directions: Soak crumbs in milk.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pack in a loaf pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: marzetti
directions: Melt shortening and brown the ground beef.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Cook until tender.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, tomato soup, tomato paste, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Place a layer of noodles in greased 3-quart casserole, then a layer of meat sauce and half of cheese.
Repeat.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 3-quart casserole uncovered in 375° oven about 45 minutes.

title: tea sandwiches
directions: Mix the chopped ingredients well together.
Spread on bread and quarter sandwiches.

title: snickers pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar and peanut butter until creamy. Stir in chopped Snickers bars. Gently fold in whipped topping just until mixed (save some Snickers bar for topping). Pour into crusts and refrigerate overnight.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix together, let stand.
Sift dry ingredients in bowl. Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture to dry ingredients.
Do not let rise. Roll out biscuits immediately or store in refrigerator.

title: souperburgers
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion in shortening until tender.
Stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Add your favorite can of cream of whatever soup and the rest of the ingredients. Cook for five minutes; stirring every now and then.
Serve on buns.
Yields 6 soupburgers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and carrots; mix well. Pour into three 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: old fashioned fruit cake
directions: Combine chopped dates, nuts, candied fruit, honey and fruit juice.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time and add to fruit mixture.
Sift flour together with salt and soda.
Mix into liquid mixture.
Put into loaf pans or tube pan. Bake in slow oven, 275° 1 1/2 hours or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Don't over bake.

title: applesauce spice squares
directions: Sift flour with baking soda and spices. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add flour mixture and then add applesauce, nuts and raisins. Mix well. Pour into 10 x 16 pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: nappa cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage; place in ice water for 45 minutes; drain.
Add water chestnuts, mushrooms and onion.
Then mix soy sauce and mayonnaise.
Pour over cabbage mixture, then add chow mein noodles. Toss and serve.

title: chicken tahitian
directions: Spray shallow baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Place chicken in dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
(One serving contains 207 calories and 27 calories from fat.)
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Stir and set aside.
Cream together the sugars and Crisco.
Add eggs, beating after each.
Add flour gradually.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Whip up oatmeal and add to creamed ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lulas chocolate cake
directions: Mix together in bowl:
sugar, flour, cocoa, soda, and salt.

title: breakfast delight
directions: Put slices of bread in bottom of flat baking pan.
Put sausage over bread in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix and pour over bread and sausage.
Cover and set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken fondesto
directions: Mix the milk, mustard, honey, salt and curry powder with the melted butter.
Place the chicken parts in a baking dish and pour the mixture over the chicken, covering each piece thoroughly. Place in a 350° oven and bake until chicken is golden, about 1 hour.
Baste the chicken with the glaze several times while baking.
(Sauce can be doubled and refrigerated and it will keep indefinitely.)

title: grape-nut dessert
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding as indicated on package.
Add Grape-Nuts cereal.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli and rice casserole(serving size: 10)
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Saute onion in margarine until onion is done.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Cut up broccoli into small pieces.
Mix rice, margarine, onion, broccoli, soup and Cheez Whiz in large bowl. Pour into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, water and pudding mix together.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Put in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Put in pudding mixture, then wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layers twice, ending with pudding. Chill.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Blend cocoa into melted butter.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool. May top with ice cream.
Yum!
Keeps well.

title: mile high pie
directions: Beat egg whites and sugar together for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice, salt and strawberries.
Whip together cream and vanilla. Fold into egg mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together last 3 ingredients; add imitation crab.
Serve with crackers.

title: raisin bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk and butter; cool to lukewarm.
Pour over sugar to dissolve it.
Add egg and dry ingredients.
Mix in drained raisins.
Let rise once.
Second time shape into 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: saucy cauliflower
directions: Cut cauliflower into flowerets.
Steam over simmering water for 6 to 8 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Meanwhile, combine all remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Place cauliflower on serving plater.
Spoon tomato sauce over the top.
Serve with broiled lamb chops, baked potatoes and lemon souffle for dessert.

title: mom's germantown oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Cream mixture.
Add all other ingredients.
Roll on a spoon the size of walnuts and bake in a 325° oven for 10 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in order given.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat, stirring until blended.
Remove from heat.
Gradually blend in milk.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until comes off bone easily in the 4 quarts of water.
Add salt and pepper.
When done remove from chicken gruel; let cool.
Add enough water to make 4 quarts gruel.
Add 2 to 3 drops yellow food coloring to gruel for color.
Mix flour, egg and buttermilk together.
Make sure dough is stiff and easy to handle; roll on a floured surface as thin as possible.
Cut in 1 1/4-inch squares.
Drop in boiling gruel; stir with wooden spoon.
After all dough is dropped in, cut off heat and cook 5 minutes.
Pick chicken off bone; add to dumplings.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub and bake sweet potatoes until soft.
Peel and cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Place slices in bottom of shallow casserole. Cut margarine in small pieces and spread over top of potatoes. Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Sprinkle sugar evenly over potatoes. Add water.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: light n' fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir constantly until gelatin is thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whip, blend in whipped topping, then whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit and chill until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust. Chill 2 hours.
You may garnish with additional fruit.

title: sweet macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
(Be sure to add required salt while cooking macaroni.)
Drain.
Put in a bowl.
Beat sugar, flour and eggs together.
Add juice drained from fruit and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add to cooked macaroni.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, add drained fruit and Cool Whip.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in 1 1/2-quart glass dish. Microwave on High 4 minutes. Stir in peanuts. Cook on High 4 more minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla. Cook 1 minute. Remove from microwave and add soda.
Should be fresh soda or it won't work right.
Pour immediately on lightly greased baking sheet.
Let stand until cool. Break into pieces.

title: bonbon pie
directions: Let ice cream soften; put into bowl and stir.
Next pour into pie shell.
Then stick Bonbons into ice cream (be sure to keep Bonbons frozen until time to use).
Cover with plastic lid and refreeze.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer and cover top with Cool Whip and drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: cornmeal scrapple
directions: Combine cornmeal, milk, sugar and salt.
Gradually stir into boiling water; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook, covered, over low heat about 10 minutes.
Crumble sausage finely; add to cornmeal mixture.
Pour into loaf pan.
Cover and chill. To serve, cut scrapple into 1/3-inch thick slices; dip in flour. Fry slowly in butter for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned, turning once.
Serve with butter and maple syrup, if desired.

title: joyce's chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chicken. Dip all chicken pieces into this mixture and place in glass baking dish. Pour remaining sauce over chicken. Cover and let sit in the refrigerator overnight. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour to 1-1/2 hours. Baste 2 or 3 times, and turn chicken once during baking.

title: baked ham slice
directions: Mix the brown sugar (loosely packed) and dry mustard together. Place the ham slice in a 2-inch deep baking dish or a cast-iron skillet.
Sprinkle with the brown sugar and dry mustard. Pour enough milk around the ham to come nearly to the top.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Has a wonderful flavor.

title: ham-mac casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Turn into greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix.
Pour into Bundt or angel cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini pie
directions: In large bowl, mix zucchini, grated cheese, garlic, basil, salt and pepper.
In another bowl, mix the Bisquick, oil and eggs. Fold into ingredients of large bowl and mix.
Put in a baking pan and sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger and
beans until hot.
Toss the lettuce, tomatoes, avocado, onion and cheese together.
Add 1 small bag taco flavored Doritos and 1/4 bottle Catalina dressing.
Toss. Add meat and beans and toss lightly.
Serve.

title: layer cake
directions: Prepare cake by package instructions and spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done.

title: polish potato pancakes
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in potatoes, onions, salt and flour.
Mix.
Drop spoonfuls into frying pan, well covered with melted oleo or butter.
Flatten and brown on both sides.
Serve with sour cream or syrup.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into 6 x 10-inch baking pan or casserole.
Remove from oven; sprinkle cheese over top and return to bake 10 to 15 minutes longer until cheese is melted.
Great with steaks, roast beef or chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, plus 10 to 15 minutes after cheese is added.

title: mary's jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add beaten eggs.
Combine soda and buttermilk; add to mixture.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in 3 layers.
Test with toothpick.

title: "easy" fudge pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt; add eggs, milk and margarine. Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour one-half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Layer more crackers and the remaining pudding mixture.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Spread frosting on top, filling in the cracks between crackers to make it smooth.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, mix soups, tomatoes, milk, onion and 6 tablespoons chicken broth.
Stir well.
Layer in Pyrex baking dish in this order:
chips, chicken, soup mixture, chips, chicken, soup mixture, etc., then top with the grated cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let set overnight in fridge before cooking.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Toss fruit and pecans with flour to coat.
Stir fruit and nuts into cake mix. Mix well.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pans greased and lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 275° for 1 and 3/4 hours or until cake tests done.
Makes 2 cakes.
Soak and baste with orange juice for a few days (2 to 3 days should be enough...too long soaking makes cake tear when cut).

title: minestrone soup
directions: Soak white beans 4 to 6 hours in 1-quart water.
Put beans and soaking liquid into stockpot.
Add celery, garlic and onion. Bring to a boil and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender. Add defatted chicken broth, red wine, olive oil, tomatoes, pepper, basil, oregano and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Add green beans, carrots and potatoes.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add macaroni.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix cucumbers with sour cream, then mix vinegar and sugar. Add to cucumbers.
Let set in refrigerator until chilled.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Bake vegetables as directed on package; drain and cut up cooked cauliflower.
Mix vegetables and place in a 1 1/2-quart Pyrex dish.
Spread cream of mushroom soup on top of vegetables; mix.
Top with cheese soup.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: celbeetato salad
directions: Cut beets and potatoes into 1/2 - 1 inch cubes.
Combine with celery.
Blend vinegar, oil and salt to make dressing.
Combine celery, beets, potatoes and salad dressing.
Slice eggs and place on top of the salad making a decorative edge.
Spoon relish on the top of the salad, inside the ring of egg slices, sort of like a bulls eye.
Serve cold as an accompaniment to a meal.
Serves: 6-8.

title: spice tea
directions: Pour water over tea and let cool.
Strain and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer mixture for 20 minutes.
If too strong add water.
Add extra sugar to taste.
This recipe makes 16 to 20 cups.

title: cherie's tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain.
Add cheese from package. Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Place shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is light brown, about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini chocolate bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Beat eggs; add milk, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Cream together.
Add sifted dry ingredients and then add chocolate chips.
Mix well. Bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: homemade salami
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make into log rolls; roll in foil. Refrigerate 24 to 36 hours.
Pierce foil with an ice pick; back on rack for 3 hours at 250°.

title: onion bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Cook macaroni in pot of water until done.
Drain.
Mix meat and macaroni together in pot.
Add sauce and chili powder.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer together about 30 minutes.

title: cornflake fish
directions: Wash filets and cut into serving pieces.
Heat frying pan and grease lightly with olive oil.

title: shortbread squares
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Combine flour and cornstarch, gradually add to creamed mixture.
Pat into ungreased 15 x 10
pan.
Pierce several times with a fork.
Bake 350° for 40 - 45 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cut while warm.
Yield about 6 dozen.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken with squash and corn
directions: Brown fryer in covered pan.
Add sliced squash, corn on cob (cut into
smaller	pieces),
garlic,
salt
and
onions. Finish cooking uncovered.	Mash
squash
and
add can of corn. Cover and finish cooking until all is tender.
Serves 8.

title: hot water gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed, dissolving soda in boiling water.
Pour into shallow, greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with Gingerbread Sauce.

title: cowboy stew(hamburger soup)
directions: Brown meat, Add other ingredients.
Cook on medium heat 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add 1 can cream style corn just before ready to serve.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In large bowl, combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, cinnamon and salt; mix well. Pour into shell. Bake 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer or until knife inserted near edge comes out clean. Cool. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well.
Make soft ball and mash flat with glass dipped in sugar.
Red and green sugar can be used for quick Christmas cookies.
Easy, fast and good!

title: spinach ricotta pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake pie shell, until lightly browned. Drain spinach and set aside.
Melt butter in saute pan and saute onion until translucent.
Stir spinach into onion and heat through.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Add spinach mixture and stir until mixture looks like green and white marble. Pour into shell and bake 45 to 55 minutes or until top is golden and set.
Serves 4.
Add salad and fresh bread and you have a great lunch or dinner.

title: meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain. Add can of soup to meat and onion, heat in skillet until soup is runny, then pour into pie crust.
Top with cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese is melted.

title: sweet potato chewies
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, flour, sugar, and milk. Beat at medium speed for one minute. Add salt & vanilla mixing well. Stir in coconut and pecans. Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan in oven at 400 degrees. Pour butter into sweet potato mixture, mixing thoroughly. Spread batter in baking dish. Bake at 400 degrees for 30-40 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, egg yolks, salt and vanilla extract.
Gradually add 1/4 cup milk.
Add remainder of 3 cups milk.
Put in double boiler.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until almost thick.
In large dish, add layers of vanilla wafers and banana slices.
Add custard.

title: april fool apple pie(using betty crocker pie crust mix)
directions: Combine pie crust mix with cold water; mix lightly with fork. Roll out half of dough on a floured board; fit into 8-inch pan. Break crackers into pastry lined pan.
Boil water, sugar and cream of tartar together for 15 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice and rind. Pour syrup over crackers.
Dot generously with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll out remaining dough for top crust. Place over filling; trim edges, seal and flute.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough milk to mix well.
Spray skillet with Pam.
Pour batter and cook until brown at 350°.

title: lemon pie(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, water and salt.
Mix together cornstarch and 1/2 cup water and add to first mixture.
Cook until thick. Combine egg yolks, lemon juice, butter and lemon peel.
Add to first mixture and cook until thick again.
Stir often.
Add 2 tablespoons of prepared meringue to filling and pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with remaining meringue and bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown on top.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix dressing according to package directions and pour over broccoli (fresh or frozen) that has been precooked 2 to 4 minutes. Let stand overnight.
This is a great compliment to any meal.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice steak
into
1-inch strips, 1/4-inch thick.
Heat olive oil in
fryer.
Add
steak, cover and cook over very low flame approximately
minutes.
Add
more
olive
oil,
if needed, to keep
fryer
from
drying out.
Put steak and mushrooms in casserole.	Add
butter
and
flour to juices left in fryer, stirring to prevent lumps.	Add sour cream and continue stirring, while over low flame, until mixed well.
Add this to meat in casserole.	Place
insert in 3-quart unit over boiling water and cook
for
minutes.
Serve
on toast, regular or English muffins or rice.

title: velvet pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add salt.
Add flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add lemon.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: banana raisin muffins
directions: Combine raisins and apple juice in a large bowl and let stand for five minutes.
Add buttermilk, egg whites, oil and honey; whisk until smooth.
Sift the flour, cornmeal, baking powder and baking soda into another large bowl.
Whisk in brown sugar, ginger and cardamom.
Add bananas and toss lightly.
Add dry ingredients to buttermilk mixture and stir just to mix with a wooden spoon.
(Stir as little as possible, or the muffins will be tough.)
Line muffin tin cups with paper liners and spray lightly with vegetable oil spray.
Spoon batter into cups, filling each two-thirds full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, until puffed and lightly browned.
Turn onto a wire rack to cool.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: *koulourakia("twist cookies")
directions: Mix together the butter, Crisco and sugar and beat for 7 minutes.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Add orange juice mixed with baking powder. Add enough flour so dough doesn't stick to hands. Knead until well blended.
Shape into an "s" shape or braid about 2 to 3-inches long.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Beat 1 egg and lightly brush the cookies.
Bake in a 325° to 350° oven (depending on oven) for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cupcake frosting
directions: Cream
sugar with butter (soft), and salt in small bowl. Blend
extract,
2 tablespoons milk and remaining sugar into mixture.
Gradually
add remaining milk to mixture until consistency desired.
Icing does 36 cupcakes.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Cook all ingredients except mayonnaise on stove.
When thick, remove from heat and add mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Pour over cooked, cut-up potatoes.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook flour and cooking oil until very light brown.
Add chopped onions and garlic.
Cook until onions are soft.
Add tomato sauce, water, shrimp, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook rice while waiting.
Add cooked rice to the mixture and simmer for 5 more minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cut wings at joints; discard tips.
Dip wings into 3 beaten eggs.
Brown.
Put into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: mrs. couragen's lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
(Cook noodles while simmering.)
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer noodles, 1/2 sauce, Velveeta cut in chunks, Mozzarella cut in chunks and Parmesan cheese; end with rest of sauce.
Top with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry vinegar
directions: Combine strawberries and vinegar in a bowl, cover and let stand at room temperature 24 hours; stir occasionally.
Strain mixture through cheesecloth and discard all seeds.
Stir in sugar and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Pour vinegar into decorative jars and seal.
Yields about 2 cups.
Serve over salads.

title: adelaides
directions: Cut the dates into 3 pieces.
Cook half of them over low heat with 2 tablespoons water until soft.
Let cool.
Cream the sugars, shortening, egg and date paste.
Sift the dry ingredients and add. Beat smooth.
Add oatmeal, if desired, and the remaining dates and walnuts.
Form into balls, dip in sugar and bake at 375°. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: baked chicken
directions: Line a greased casserole dish (9 x 13-inch) with dried beef. Place chicken on top with bacon strip on each chicken piece.
Mix soup.
Add milk and sour cream.
Pour over all.
Place in cold oven at 250° and bake for 4 hours, uncovered.
Serve over rice, noodles or pasta.

title: top of stove cookies
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients in saucepan over medium heat and bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute only.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix quickly.
Drop teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let harden at room temperature.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Bake for 2 hours at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour then add egg yolks and milk. Cook on high, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly. Add vanilla. Layer cookies then bananas then pour pudding over both. Top with meringue. Bake until golden brown.

title: gob cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions plus add to previous ingredients oil, egg yolks and chocolate pudding.
Mix well.
Line a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with wax paper.
Bake as directed on cake mix box.
Cool cake.
Cut horizontally into two layers.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all together in blender. Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a pie pan.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cream tomato soup
directions: Melt cheese and soup over low heat.
Dissolve gelatin in 2 Tbsp. water.
Add to hot mixture.
When cool, add mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Stir in solids.
Pour in mold.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Remove excess fat from chops; roll in flour (do not brown). Place in baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, catsup and mustard. Put 1/4 mixture on each chop.
Add water to come up 1/4 way of pork chops.
Do not cover with water.
Cover pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking 15 minutes to brown. Add more water as needed during baking.

title: muffins
directions: Blend egg, milk and oil; set aside.
In another bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add to wet ingredients and stir.
You can add blueberries or just leave plain.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full and bake in a 375° to 400° oven.

title: liverwurst pate
directions: Mash and blend or beat until smooth.
Chill 4 hours.
This will keep for two weeks, refrigerated.

title: holiday cranberry dessert
directions: Rinse cranberries and drain.
Grind two oranges with the rinds on and peel the other oranges and grind.
Peel apples and grind. Grind cranberries also.
Mix cranberries, apples, oranges and crushed pineapple with juice and add sugar.
Chill.

title: bacon potato soup
directions: Spray a saucepan with nonstick cooking spray.
Add onions and bacon.
Cook and stir over medium heat until onion is tender but not brown.
Stir in water and potatoes.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Use a fork and mash some potatoes.
Stir in milk, butter seasoning, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until heated through.
Do not boil.
Ladle into bowls; serve with light sour cream and chives, if desired.

title: apple salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add dry Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese, stirring until mixed well.
Cool. Fold in apples, nuts, celery and whipped topping.
Pour into 9-inch baking pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares. Serve on lettuce leaves with crackers.

title: wild rice chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Melt butter.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in half and half and broth.
Cook; stir constantly until thickened.
Stir in chicken, pimento, parsley, almonds and cooked rice.
Pour in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Mix egg, water and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture; stir with fork.
Makes 5 crusts. Bake at 425°.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in oatmeal. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple muffins
directions: Grate apples and set aside.
In bowl, beat eggs, add sweetener, extracts and spices.
Crumble bread into mixture.
Mix. Blend in apples and spoon into 6 paper muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before removing from pans.

title: miss bessie's chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt; then set aside.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in a greased pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: brian's favorite sunday breakfast
directions: Cook sausages in frying pan until well done.
Drain off fat. Add fruit cocktail to frying pan, scraping brown bits into the fruit and syrup.
Serve sausage and fruit cocktail warm.
Serve with buttered toast.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and press in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine the next four ingredients and place over the first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut in small squares.

title: lemon marinated chicken
directions: In a shallow dish, combine all ingredients except chicken; mix well.
Add chicken; turn to coat.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 20 to 30 minutes, the longer, the better.
Oil broiler pan and place chicken on prepared pan; broil 4 to 6 inches from broiler.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes on one side, basting with marinade.
Turn and continue cooking and basting 8 to 10 minutes longer or until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear.
Can also be charcoal grilled.
Use same method as for broiling. Serves 4.

title: orange terrine(good for diabetics)
directions: Line bottom and sides of 8-inch loaf pan with plastic wrap. Stand ladyfingers, enough to fit evenly along 2 sides of pan (cut sides should be facing in).

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: May omit nuts and add 1/2 cup coconut, raisins and 1/4 cup evaporated milk, if desired.

title: south of the border chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, combine chicken, tomatoes, red onion, jicama, cilantro and lime juice. Toss together well.
Garnish with slices of avocado, season with salt and pepper and serve immediately.

title: patty's potato soup
directions: Add potatoes, onions, corn and butter into a medium stewing pot filled halfway up with water.
Cook on medium heat for approximately 60 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes and add water if needed to avoid scorching.
When potatoes are soft to the touch, add milk and cook on low for approximately 15 minutes.
Dish into bowls.
Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then add orange slices. When ready to serve, add sherbet.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature. Combine ingredients and roll into the 1/2 cup chopped pecans.

title: hearty chicken cheese chowder
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Do not drain.
Melt butter in separate saucepan.
Add flour and stir.
Gradually add milk and stir until thick.
Add cheese; stir.
Stir cheese sauce into vegetable mixture.
Add chicken and heat through; do not boil.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread graham cracker crumbs evenly over butter.
Spread coconut over crust.
Then spread evenly, in layers, the chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, condensed milk and chopped nuts.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Cool. Cut into 1 or 1 1/2 inch squares.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken; cut into pieces.
Add onion, soup, margarine, cheese and broccoli.
Sprinkle croutons and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: no-crust pecan pie
directions: Chop fine or grind pecans.
Crumble wafers.
Mix them well with sugar.
Beat egg whites until stiff (peaks).
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture into well buttered glass pie pan.
Cook in a preheated 350° oven for 25 or 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: frijoles diablo a la nick
directions: Saute onions and peppers.
Add garlic and jalapenos.
Cook until soft and golden.
Stir in beans and spices.
Heat through and serve.
You may want to bake in oven about 30 minutes to blend flavors together even more.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix together the first five ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Pie will not be firm when cooked, but will firm up.
Makes 8 servings.

title: e-z potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add cream cheese and beat.
Add egg and milk.
Beat. Add onion and seasoning.
Place in casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Can be prepared the day before and baked the next day.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter in pie pan and then pour in bowl. Add sugar and then eggs. Blend in vanilla and flour. Mix with cocoa. Pour in pie pan (buttered and floured). Bake in a 325° oven until set. Serve plain or with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream. Nuts may be added.

title: laura's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together first 6 items, then add flour, soda and salt and mix well.
Add raisins and oats; mix well.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown at 350° on greased cookie sheet.

title: friendship cake - sourdough starter
directions: Melt butter, add other ingredients and drop on top of cake. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool completely before turning out of pan.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Make custard according to box directions and chill.
Add 1/2 box of frozen blueberries or 1 cup fresh blueberries.
Mix together lemon juice, lemon rind, cornstarch and sugar.
Thicken over low heat.
Add 1 cup (1/2 box) of blueberries and cook slightly.
Chill cooked mixture.

title: barbecued short ribs
directions: Brown short ribs in the fat.
Make a sauce by simmering together for 20 minutes the onion, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and water.
Pour sauce over the browned ribs; cover and let simmer in a slow oven at 325° for 2 hours.
Add water if needed.
Serves 6.

title: quick manhattan clam chowder
directions: Cook and stir bacon and onion in large saucepan until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Mix in remaining ingredients and heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to box directions.
Drain well. Mix with soup, rice, mayonnaise and chestnuts.
Pour into greased casserole dish and put crumbs that have been mixed with melted oleo on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Serves 10.

title: crunchy cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium size serving bowl. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 3 cups or 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: halibut
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a shallow baking dish large enough to hold fish in a single layer.
Season fish with salt and pepper.
Arrange in prepared dish.
Sprinkle with orange peel and basil, then dot with butter.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, basting occasionally with pan juices spooned over.
Makes 4 servings.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Lightly brown hamburger. Drain beans and combine with beef mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins and cool.
In saucepan over low heat, combine cheese and butter.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat and blend sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Shred potatoes coarsely and fold into the cheese mixture.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven.
Can be made the day ahead and baked just before serving or freeze and bake at serving time.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecued fried chicken
directions: Coat each piece of chicken with flour.
Fry in shortening until golden.
Blend together small amount of water with 2 tablespoons flour.
Add remaining water.
Mix well with remaining ingredients. Drain excess fat from chicken.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit dream
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a medium bowl.
Sprinkle 3 more walnut halves, chopped, on top.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Soften cream cheese; whip for 1 minute.
Mix together cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, soup, garlic, milk, salt and pepper. Whip until creamy.
Cut up chicken and mix with broccoli.
Pour creamy mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread *
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and eggs. Put soda into milk and beat into meal mixture.
Mix in peppers, half of cheese and corn. Put oil in skillet, and pour in batter.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Bake in hot oven.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; crumble and set aside. Reserve 3 tablespoons bacon drippings in saucepan.
Add onion slices to pan and cook until lightly brown.
Add diced potatoes and water; cook over medium heat until tender.
Add corn, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook until heated through.
Pour into serving bowls; top with crumbled bacon and margarine.
Serve with crackers.
Serve 4 to 5.

title: rot kraut (red cabbage)
directions: Melt shortening.
Add shredded cabbage, chopped apples and water.
Cook until tender.
Add blended flour, vinegar, sugar and seasoning.
Cook a few minutes longer.

title: sago cooler
directions: Bring 6 cups water to a boil.
Add sago.
Lower heat to moderate and cook until sago becomes clear.
Drain.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix together sugar, syrup and peanuts.
Cook over medium heat until syrup spins a thread.
Cook until a golden brown. Take off stove and stir in soda. Work quickly.
Spread on flat buttered dish. Cool and break into pieces.

title: fruit cooler
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender.
Makes a wonderful breakfast drink or snack between meals.

title: genny's simple dip
directions: Put cream cheese on serving plate.
Pour jalapeno jelly on top of cream cheese letting it run down the sides.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: sauerkraut and potato cake(german)
directions: Beat the egg yolks separately; mix the yolks and rest of ingredients.
Beat the whites of the eggs until stiff.
Fold in 1 can of rinsed sauerkraut, drained well.
Add egg whites and nuts. Bake in a tube cake pan for 1 hour or until tested done.
Serves 12.

title: beef brisket
directions: Simmer in covered pan on top of stove for 4 to 4 1/2 hours. Every hour, turn brisket over.
Last hour, end with fat side down. Serve with broth from pan.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mash sausage and cook with onions until brown.
Put onion and sausage mixture in bowl.
Do not drain. Break bread into pieces. Put most of bread into sausage mixture.
Save remaining bread for top.
Add ketchup.
Dip remaining bread pieces in grease from sausage mixture.
Set aside.
Boil green peppers until tender. Fill with stuffing.
Set oven at 350 degrees, leave approximately 1 inch water in pan.
Bake until bread crumbs are brown.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Mix well with mixer.
Press into a mold.
Let stand awhile to blend flavors.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas, one at a time.
In another bowl, cream oleo. Add sour cream, sugar, flour, vanilla, soda and salt; mix with mixer.
Blend in pecans and bananas.
Put into greased loaf or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes, then turn out onto plate.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn, green pepper and tomato sauce.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Prepare muffin mix and add to it the crumbled French fried onions.
Spoon muffin mixture over meat filling in dish; smoothing it even and to the edge of dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Flour and lightly brown chicken.
Saute vegetables in chicken drippings for about 5 minutes.
Add small amount of flour to make a roux and stir.
Combine chicken, sausage, vegetables, roux and water in a large pot.
Cook over low heat for around 2 hours. Serve soup over rice.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet potato croquettes
directions: Cook, peel and mash sweet potatoes.
Add flour, salt and egg; mix well.
Chill mixture in refrigerator overnight.
Place bread crumbs on a piece of wax paper.
With spoon, put enough mixture into crumbs to form a log about 2-inches long and 3/4-inches in diameter.
Coat entire log with crumbs.
Lay single on flat try and chill before frying in deep oil (use deep fryer).

title: deep dish crab quiche
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 425°.
Toss together cheese and flour.
Combine milk, eggs, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add crab, cheese mixture and spinach to milk mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake an additional 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 6.

title: orange wine sauce(serve with pork)
directions: Melt butter, add flour.
Stir in juice, slowly, then wine. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add brown sugar and salt.

title: half-a-pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla. Combine cake flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Add milk and beat 5 minutes.
Pour batter into
a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or into 2 smaller loaf pans.
Bake.

title: pork in cider sauce
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, brown pork in oil; drain off oil.
Add the first 1/2 cup cider and onion.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 40 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Combine cornstarch, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon in a bowl.
Blend in the remaining 1/2 cup cider and vinegar.
Add to pork mixture, along with apple.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened, then cook and stir about 2 minutes more.
Serve over hot rice or warm noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: ranch flavored popcorn
directions: Pop the corn.
Mix together dill, garlic, oil and dressing mix.
Add popped corn to oil mixture.
Shake well to coat.
Let stand 1 hour.
Store covered.

title: herbed green beans
directions: Cut beans 1 1/2 to 2-inches.
Steam them until tender.
Chop the rosemary and sage.
Mix together the herbs, olive oil, lemon juice and garlic in a small bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: quilter's pickles
directions: Drain liquid from the jar of dill pickles.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Then add mayonnaise and mix until well blended.
Scoop crab salad into avocado halves and serve on bed of lettuce.

title: marinade for chicken
directions: Chicken breasts work the best.
Pour Catalina or French salad dressing over chicken and let set in refrigerator overnight or for at least 2 to 4 hours.

title: grape juice (canned)
directions: Wash and remove stems of fresh Concord grapes (firm and ripe). Place 1 cup grapes into hot quart jar.
Add sugar.
Fill jar with boiling water, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust covers and caps.
Process quart in water bath for 10 minutes.
Allow to set for 1 to 2 months before using.

title: martha pafford's sawmill gravy
directions: Place oil in frypan on medium-high.
Add flour; brown lightly. Add beaten eggs, stirring, then add water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot over grits or biscuits.
If too thick, add more water.

title: diabetic salad
directions: Mix yogurt and pudding together.
Add pineapple and mix well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: whatever is in the garden stir-fry
directions: Put rice on to cook according to directions.
Thinly slice chicken or beef.
Heat wok or large skillet.
Add small amount of oil.
Add meat.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove.
Set aside.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash and add oleo after drained.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Put in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix together chuck, soup mix, egg, Accent and bread crumbs. Form into bite size meatballs.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
In a large skillet, over medium heat, mix ketchup and apple jelly until blended.
Add meatballs, cover and simmer 25 minutes. Serve in chafing dish.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples that have been diced and sugar.
Add oil, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Set aside.
Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add this mixture to green apple mixture and stir well. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour (maybe more) at 350°. Frosting is not needed.

title: italian vegetables
directions: Wash and clean vegetables.
Cut zucchini and carrots into 1-inch slices.
Cut onion into wedges.
Put all ingredients into saucepan or large Pyrex dish and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender.
Serve as a vegetable dish or over pasta.

title: plump molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add molasses; blend well.
Mix and sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add boiling water; mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes (press each cookie before baking with bottom of a glass that's covered with a damp cloth).

title: batter mix for frying
directions: Stir all together. Dip meat into. Fry in deep oil.

title: baked peas
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Whip the can of milk.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crust (mix crumbs with butter, then line pan with mixture).
Add cheese to warm jello.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in milk (that has been whipped).
Pour into pan and chill.
Top with cherry pie filling if desired.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano.
Add ground turkey.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Place 1/2 the spaghetti in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/2 the vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of the Cheddar cheese. Repeat the layers.
Mix the soup and water until smooth.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 12 servings (low fat).

title: quick and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small baking dish (about 8 x 8-inch dish), melt butter in oven.
Add pie filling to butter.

title: the perfect sugar cookie
directions: Mix each ingredient with a wooden spoon as you go.
If dough is sticky, add 1/2 cup flour more.
Roll on floured board. Dough should be about 1/8-inch thick.
Use floured cookie cutters and cut out cookie shapes. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cookies should not be browned or golden.
When cool, frost with frosting glaze.

title: dill macaroni salad
directions: Or use 1 small bottle Green Goddess dressing.

title: spinach tortellini soup
directions: Combine onion, carrot and broth; bring to a boil. Add tortellini; reduce heat. Simmer 4 minutes. Add spinach; stir and simmer 4 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Crumble crackers in bowl.
Pour water over crackers.
Set aside for 1/2 hour.
Then mix hamburger with onion.
Add the crackers and mix together with hands.
Pat into 13 x 9 inch pan. Cover and let set until next day.
Then cut into squares.
Flour them individually and brown in oil in skillet.
When brown, remove to a large pan or casserole dish and spoon a can of mushroom soup over all the meat.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli raisin salad
directions: Mix broccoli, raisins, bacon and onion together.
Make dressing with mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add dressing and toss just before serving.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Blend until smooth cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, mayonnaise and onion.
Spread mixture on pizza pan.
Top with chili sauce and shrimp.
Serve on crackers.

title: tropical tuna melt(microwave recipe)
directions: Drain pineapple very well.
Save 1 teaspoon pineapple juice. Stir together salad dressing (or mayonnaise), mustard and pineapple juice.
Using small bowl, stir together drained pineapple, tuna and celery and dressing mixture.
Arrange toasted English muffins in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top each muffin half with 1/4 of tuna mixture.
Top with 1/2 diagonally sliced cheese.
Cook in microwave on High 1
to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn once while cooking. Serves 4.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in large baking dish except potatoes. Cover and bake in 300° oven 2 1/4 hours; add potatoes and continue baking for 45 minutes more.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Melt butter in 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Put peaches over batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 400° or until light brown.

title: deer stir-fry
directions: Put meat strips in skillet with a little cooking oil and stir until almost done.
Add pepper, onion and garlic and stir occasionally until pepper and onion is sauteed.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until well seasoned.
Serve over rice or alone.

title: orange and almond chicken
directions: Prepare grill at least 1/2 hour before cooking time.
Adjust grid 6 to 8 inches above the coals.
Rinse chicken parts; pat dry. In small bowl, blend ingredients to form a paste.
Gently lift chicken skin; spread paste as evenly as possible between skin and meat.
Place chicken skin-side up on grill.
Grill 20 to 30 minutes, until chicken is no longer pink when cut near bone.
Turn chicken once, halfway through cooking period.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Mix the green onions and slaw together.
Break up the noodles and add to the slaw.
Mix the oil, vinegar and sugar together. Add the spices from the noodles.
Pour this over the slaw.
Add the nuts and seeds just before serving.
It works well to make this slaw a day before you are going to serve it.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
Mix all ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour over carrots.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Put in cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine milk, 2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce and soup mix. Blend well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add beef and mix well.
Mixture will be moist.
Shape into balls, using 1 tablespoon for each. Place on a rack.
Broil 5 to 6 minutes; do not turn.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Slice pound of bacon in half.
Put 5 to 6 green beans on each half slice of bacon and roll up.
Place bean bundles on cookie sheet.
Cover with dressing and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk into a paste-like mixture.
Pour mixture over melted butter. Add the can of peaches.
Add water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and vanilla. Gradually add sugar. Beat well.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll in log shape as for refrigerator cookies and chill. Slice as needed and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: baked banana
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice bananas lengthwise and place in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle each with lemon juice. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 25 minutes.
Garnish with lemon wedges.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix ingredients; cover and chill.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Fry bacon crisp and break up.
Cut cheese into cubes (small).
Mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise well, then add broccoli, bacon and cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, salt and vinegar in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until sugar dissolves.

title: sausage appetizer
directions: Cut sausage links diagonally into bite size pieces.
Mix peach preserves and mustard in saucepan and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add sausage and simmer for 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: carla and mel's lemon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: basic waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron.
Put in blender; process on high until mixed.
Overbeating will make waffles tough.
Pour batter into waffle iron and cook.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat peanut butter and applesauce together, then add sugars and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking powder and soda.
Add to other mixture and mix until just moistened.
Stir in oatmeal, applesauce and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased pan and bake 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: steak casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water; drain and rinse. Combine the mushroom soup, milk, onions and seasonings.
Alternate layers of macaroni, soup and cheese in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or can microwave.

title: chicken breasts with mushrooms
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in beaten eggs, salt and pepper for 1 hour.
Bread chicken in crumbs and saute in butter until golden brown.
Cover with sauteed mushrooms and cheese.
Baste with wine or chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan; place peaches in bottom of pan and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; set aside.

title: spinach rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Transfer to large bowl.
Cool slightly.
Combine dressing, soy sauce and sugar. Stir into warm rice.
Cover and chill.
Fold in remaining ingredients before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a large mixing bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
(Dough will be sticky).
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface, and knead 5 to 10 times.
Cover and let rise at least 30 minutes.

title: sammie's caramel praline pie
directions: Brown coconut and pecans in margarine.
Set aside to cool. Combine the cream cheese, milk and half of a carton of Cool Whip. Layer cream cheese mixture on bottom, then layer pecan mixture. Next drizzle caramel on top of other layers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Freeze for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: linguine salad
directions: Rinse linguine noodles in cold water until noodles are cold. Add and mix with noodles the remaining ingredients except for the cucumber and tomato; add these prior to serving.
Let stand for 8 hours in refrigerator prior to serving.

title: kids' cupcake mountain
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Prepare muffin tins with liners. Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Fork-sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed ingredients a portion at a time.
Use milk proportionately until well mixed.
Fill liners 2/3 full.
Bake for around 20 minutes or until brown on top.
Test with toothpick to see if they are done. Cool.
Frost with Chocolate Buttercream Frosting.
When the frosting is dry, arrange your cupcakes in 3 or 4 tiers.
You will build a "cake" out the cupcakes.
Begin with 7 cupcakes in a circle for the bottom.
Scatter M&M's over this layer.
Add a tier of 4, then 3, then 1!
Scatter more M&M's plus sprinkles to decorate.

title: noodle cheese casserole
directions: Break the noodles into 1 1/2-inch pieces; cook in the boiling, salted water until tender, about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Drain thoroughly.
Heat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, saute onion and green pepper in butter for about 3 minutes.
Stir in the flour and seasonings, then stir in the milk gradually and cook, stirring, until the sauce is smooth and thick.
Grease a 2-quart casserole. Turn the sauce into it.
Add noodles, cottage cheese and lemon juice; toss until well blended.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes and boil until just done (don't let them get mushy).
Cut into cubes (leave skin on).
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with onion, reserving a few to sprinkle on top.
Warm soup and sour cream and pour over potatoes.
Mix gently.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 325° until thoroughly heated and cheese has melted.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except marshmallow cream.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x
2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
While cake
is
hot
spread marshmallow cream on top. Let cool, then
add
Mississippi
Mud
Topping. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: creamed zucchini and corn
directions: Combine the undrained corn, zucchini, mushrooms, pimento and bouillon.
Cook (covered) oven medium heat until tender.
Blend together the sour cream, flour, dill weed and salt.
Stir into hot mixture and cook an additional 15 minutes or until heated through. Stir occasionally.

title: bread pudding(diabetic recipe)
directions: Place bread cubes in 1-quart casserole coated with Pam. Sprinkle with raisins.
Set aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and let refrigerate overnight.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix together. Boil 20 minutes and put into jars and seal.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes until almost done.
Do not drain water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Serve.

title: lemon cream bars
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine first 2 ingredients; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine all other ingredients.
Mix at low speed until crumbly.
Press half of crumb mixture into prepared pan.
Spread lemon mixture on.
Crumble remaining mixture over all.
Bake in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown. Cut into bars.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: charleston apple crumb pie
directions: Mix sugar and nutmeg.
Pour this over thinly sliced apples and put in deep dish, unbaked pie crust.
Cut butter into brown sugar and flour until crumbly.
Pat the crumb mixture over apples and top with milk.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until done, about 35 minutes.

title: spice cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside. In large bowl, beat together margarine, sugar and egg whites.
Add flour mixture and beat until combined.
Mix in cereal.
Drop by level tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes or until light brown.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in the applesauce, sugar, oil and milk.
Gradually add the dry ingredients which have been mixed together to the egg mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in 1 cup finely chopped pecans (optional) and the 1/2 cup mixed fruit (optional). Spread in well-greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Puree tomatoes in blender.
Pour into a large bowl.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Chop onions very fine.
Add to tomatoes along with garlic powder and salt.
May add more garlic and salt to taste.
Serve with corn chips.

title: venison cutlets
directions: Season steaks with salt and pepper and roll in bread crumbs. Melt shortening in skillet and fry steaks until well browned on both sides.
Place on a hot platter.
Make a gravy with drippings remaining in pan and add 1/4 cup currant jelly.
Pour over steaks. Serve with currant jelly or apples cooked in a Port wine.
Allow 1/2 to 3/4 pound per person.

title: healthy italian dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients; shake well.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Put onion, celery, green peppers, garlic and butter in pan. Cook until onions are transparent.
Add remaining ingredients and cook.
Serve over rice.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Chop cabbage. Steam or put in soup raw as you like.
Combine all other ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce flame and simmer.

title: strawberry delight(low-fat for diabetics)
directions: Crush strawberries. Add a couple drops of red food coloring, if desired.
Beat in pudding and mix until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust; sprinkle with coconut. Chill.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar in a saucepan over low heat. Remove from stove and add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.
Best if baked the day you serve them.

title: dinner dippers
directions: Have children flatten biscuits.
Then have them place meat and cheese on each biscuit and wrap biscuit around the meat and cheese, sealing all edges.
Place on greased cookie sheet and brush each dipper with melted butter or margarine.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until nicely browned.
Serve with a dipping sauce of your choice.
Serves 4.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until for my. Add sugar, beat until thick. Add 6 cups milk and salt. Mix well. Pour egg mixture in large sauce pan and place over low heat. Stir constantly until well heated. Do Not Boil. Remove from heat and add half and half and eagle brand milk and vanilla. Mix well. Add fruit and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: meal-in-one-casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish with layer of frozen Potato Puffs or hash brown potatoes.
Drain green beans and place on top of Potato Puffs. Top green beans with ham.
End with another layer of Potato Puffs.

title: haystacks
directions: In a bowl, mix peanuts and noodles.
Melt morsels over hot water (not boiling). Pour over peanut noodles mixture and drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Let haystacks harden or "set up."

title: creamy apple graham squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine all crust ingredients.
With pastry blender or mixer at low speed, blend until crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups for topping.
Pat remainder in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, shortening and salt. Knead as a pie crust. Save 1/2 cup crumbs for top of cake.
Add sour milk, soda, egg and vanilla. Blend well. Bake in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lime pickles
directions: In crock or stone jar or porcelain container, combine cucumbers and lime.
Cover with cold water and let stand 24 hours, stirring lime from bottom 4 or 5 times.
Wash 5 times in cold water.
The last time, let spigot run and hold pickles in hands to be sure all lime is removed.
Let stand in lots of water for 20 minutes; drain.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix butter and sugar, then add peanut butter.
When well creamed, add 1 cup Rice Krispies at a time and mix well.
Form into small balls.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: parmesan-potato fans
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a small bowl; set aside. Wash potatoes; pat dry.
Cut each potato crosswise into 1/4-inch thick slices, cutting to, but not through, bottom of potato. Allow potatoes to stand in ice water for 10 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine in blender. Keep in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream together brown sugar, white sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add cream mixture to dry ingredients; cinnamon, soda, salt and flour.
Add oats.
Bake at 350° until done and toothpick comes out clean. Frost with favorite icing.

title: frito pie
directions: Use 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish. Add in this order: Fritos, onion, green chilies and cheese. Mix soup with 1/2 can of water and add to evaporated milk. Pour over top of other ingredients. Sprinkle chili powder over top and bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated steaks
directions: Combine ingredients in large Ziploc bag and put in refrigerator overnight.
Take out of bag and broil contents of bag together until tender.

title: velveeta chicken
directions: Prepare stuffing mix using package directions.
Combine next 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Layer chicken, cheese mixture and stuffing in 9 x 11-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Cook and stir garlic, pepper, mushrooms and onion in oil (about 5 minutes). Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder and cumin.
Heat to a boil. Reduce heat to low; add beans, zucchini and corn.
Simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
If desired, add 1 cup cheese. Stir until melted. Top with remaining cheese upon serving.

title: deviled crab mexicana
directions: Melt butter and saute onion.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, sugar, Worcestershire, Tabasco and garlic powder.
Let come to boil.
Pour over crackers and corn bread crumbs; toss lightly. Add crabmeat and put into crab shells or bake as a casserole in 9 x 13 dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugars, vanilla, water and eggs until fluffy. Mix flour with soda and salt.
Blend into butter mixture.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop 2-inches apart from teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: german macaroni salad
directions: In big bowl, combine macaroni, carrots and peas, pickle relish, onions, pepper, pickles and hot dogs.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Cook squash, covered, in a small amount of boiling, salted water, 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain well and mash. Combine squash and next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Shape mixture into 12 croquettes.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep hot oil (375°) for 3 to 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar. Pat into the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. Save 1/2 cup for the topping.

title: zucchini italian style
directions: Wash, trim and coarsely chop zucchini.
Heat oil in wok.
Add onion and zucchini.
Stir-fry about 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, Italian herbs, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and steam 4 to 5 minutes or until zucchini is still slightly crisp. Stir in cheese and stir-fry about 30 seconds.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; drain.
Mix with other ingredients and simmer 2 to 4 hours.

title: turtle pecan pie
directions: Combine chocolate crumbs and butter.
Firmly press into 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Freeze 15 minutes.

title: italian pasta
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Mix macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Serve on salad greens if desired.
Makes about 4 servings.
Can be made without the meat.
It's a great salad.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread coconut and nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour over coconut and nuts. Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Microwave all except popcorn for 2 minutes.
Remove and add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda; stir.
Put popcorn in brown paper bag sprayed with Pam.
Pour syrup mixture over popcorn.
Fold bag loosely and microwave 4 minutes stopping every minute to shake bag.
Tear open bag and cool.

title: slushy punch
directions: Boil 2 cups of water.
Add to Jell-O and dissolve.
Mix all together the Jell-O mixture and all fruit juices.

title: yogurt vinaigrette
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Then whisk in 3/4 cup plain nonfat yogurt.

title: egg brunch
directions: Spray pan.
Dice bread into small cubes.
Place in bottom of pan.

title: jamaican jungle bread
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add to dry mixture.
Bake in greased bread pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes one large loaf or two medium loaves.

title: foiled fish dinners
directions: Place fish steaks on squares of heavy foil.
Sprinkle with seasonings and lemon or lime juice.
Put several slices of potatoes and onions over fish.
Add more salt and pepper, if desired.
Top with a pat of butter.
Seal the pockets with a double fold of foil and grill over charcoal for about 20 minutes or bake in oven at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: rainbow cookies
directions: Grease bottoms of three 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Line pans with waxed paper; grease paper.

title: eggplant caviar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large shallow baking pan, bake eggplant for 60 minutes or until tender.
Cool slightly and peel. In blender or food processor, puree eggplant.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Served chilled or at room temperature with crackers. Makes 2 cups of "caviar".

title: chicken fajita baked potato
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cook sweet pepper and onion in hot margarine over medium heat until tender.
Add taco seasoning mix.
Cook and stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken, cheeses, olives and chili peppers.
Cut a lengthwise slit in the top of each potato.
Press open.
Divide chicken mixture among potatoes.
Spoon salsa over each.
Cover; cook on High (microwave) until heated through.
Serve with sour cream, guacamole and salsa.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stew broccoli 4 minutes and drain.
Put in casserole dish; add cheese and chestnuts.
Combine soup, milk and mushrooms and pour over broccoli.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with onion rings and bake 3 minutes longer.

title: plain taffy
directions: Boil until hard ball in cold water.
Pour onto buttered plate until cool enough to
pull.

title: angel custard dessert
directions: Make a custard of egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar, lemon juice and rind.
Cook over hot, not boiling water, until mixture coats the spoon.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin softened in cold water. Fold in egg whites, beaten with 3/4 cup sugar.

title: date nut cake
directions: Add chopped dates to hot water and cook until soft.
Let cool and add soda.
Stir.

title: lemon strawberry punch
directions: Dilute lemonade as directed on package.
Add thawed strawberries, ginger ale and ice cubes.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: sausage crumble
directions: Brown sausage. Drain most of the drippings. Saute onion and celery in drippings.
Add water chestnuts, soup, rice and 1 cup of water. Season. Add mushroom pieces and sausage. Mix well. Add 1 cup boiling water. Grease a casserole. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: tallerine
directions: Brown meat with onions and bell pepper.
Add garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Put 1/2 cooked noodles in large casserole dish.
Spread meat, corn and cheese over noodles.
Pour soup, 1/2 can water and tomatoes over noodles.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Just before you remove from oven, sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quiche
directions: *Sharp cheese is also good.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll out and cut.
Additional flour may be added, if needed.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly brown.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: deviled baked steak
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Cut into serving size pieces. Combine flour, mustard, salt and pepper; pound steak.
In a skillet, brown steak half at a time in oil.
Place meat in a large baking dish; top with onion.
