Combine tomatoes, carrots, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce; pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat to a serving platter.
If desired, simmer tomato-onion mixture until it is reduced to a thick gravy.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a very large container.

title: nutty apple bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Stir just enough to moisten. Pour batter into a greased loaf pan. Bake in a preheated 300° oven 1 hour or until done.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Add whipped topping and mix well.
Spread into crust.
In another bowl, beat milk and pudding mixes on low speed until combined; beat on high for 2 minutes.
Let stand for 3 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Chill.
Garnish with nuts and/or whipped topping if desired. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: edible play dough
directions: Combine peanut butter and corn syrup in large bowl; mix until smooth.
Mix confectioners sugar and dry milk in small bowl.
Add confectioners sugar mixture to peanut butter mixture, mix well. May add enough additional confectioners sugar to make of consistency of play dough.
Let kids create dummy sculptures and then gobble them up.
Yields 2 1/2 to 3 cups.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat milk, salt, sugar and nutmeg into eggs.
Add coconut. Pour into chilled pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: scotch chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt into mixing bowl.
Put oleo, oil, water and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to rapid boil.	Pour over flour
mixture.
Beat
well.
Add
rest
of ingredients. Beat well.
Pour
into
greased 11 x 16 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Ice when cool.

title: mexican chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Slowly blend coffee and cocoa; let cool. Sift sugar, flour, salt and soda.
Place in a large bowl.
Make a well in center; add oil, egg yolks, vanilla and coffee mixture. Beat until smooth.

title: spoon butter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in two cups warm water.
Melt butter and sugar together.
Add beaten egg.
Pour this mixture into water and yeast.
Mix in flour.
Drop by spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
These rolls do not have to rise because the key is the self-rising flour.

title: freeze and bake rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add 2 teaspoons sugar; let stand for 5 minutes.
Add milk, oil, salt and remaining sugar.
Add enough flour to form a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down.
Divide into four pieces.
Cover three pieces with plastic wrap.
Divide one piece into 12 balls. Place rolls on greased baking sheets; brush with melted butter. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 20 to 30 minutes.
To serve immediately, bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
To freeze for later use, partially bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Allow to cool; freeze.
Reheat frozen rolls at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: mrs. field's cookies(makes 110 cookies)
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add melted butter and rest of ingredients except Marshmallow Creme
; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake, covered in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Grease casserole.
Layer ingredients in casserole and pour eggs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until slightly brown.

title: easy macaroni casserole
directions: Mix macaroni and cheese according to box instructions.
Brown hamburger and onion together; drain excess grease.
Add ketchup, peas and corn.
Add macaroni and cheese mixture.
Pour into ovenproof dish and bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken breasts spectacular
directions: Sprinkle boned chicken breasts with garlic salt.
Let stand about 30 minutes for garlic to absorb.
Roll 1 piece of bacon around each breast.
Dip in melted butter and roll in crushed potato chips.
(Use 3/4 stick of butter and 6 ounces of potato chips
for 8 split breasts.)
Bake, uncovered, on cookie sheet for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apricot salad
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together for 5 minutes and cool. Mix cream cheese, baby food and sugar.
Add the cheese mixture to the slightly set Jell-O.
Then add the Cool Whip and pecans.
This makes a large recipe, to make a smaller salad, use 1/2 cup less water.

title: mushroom pilaf
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in rice to coat. Add soups and mushrooms; mix.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour. Stir occasionally.
Remove; sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together	butter, Crisco and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately the
dry mixture and milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes in a tube pan.

title: westhaven cake
directions: Combine dates and boiling water; cool.
Add soda into date mixture.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Sift together the salt, cocoa and flour.
Add egg and date mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a greased and floured pan at 350°.

title: fruited cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into round ball.
Serve with fresh fruit, sliced.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender.
Blend until ice cubes are crushed.

title: party punch
directions: Mix well and freeze in 1/2-gallon containers.
Makes 3 containers of frozen mixture.
Remove from freezer 3 to 4 hours before serving time.
Place in punch bowl.
When ready to serve, add chilled 7-Up or ginger ale to each 1/2 gallon.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine bay leaf and a small amount of water in a saucepan; boil.
Arrange zucchini in a steaming rack or colander.
Reduce heat and place rack in the saucepan.
Cover and steam 8 minutes until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Set aside.
Combine eggs and next 7 ingredients in a large bowl; stir to mix.
Add zucchini, tomatoes and bacon; stir gently to mix.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh limeade
directions: Squeeze limes.
When you have 2 cups juice, pour into a gallon pitcher.
Add sugar and stir.
Add enough water to make 1 gallon. Taste and adjust sugar if you like it sweeter.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Grease tube pan or 2 loaf pans. Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add applesauce and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Fold in nuts, if using.
Turn into prepared pan(s).
Bake for 60 minutes or when center springs back to touch.

title: mary leone's summer cold appetizer
directions: Roast peppers on foil-lined tray in broiler.
Turn with tongs until skin is blackened on all sides, then put peppers in a brown paper bag for 15 to 20 minutes to cool.
Remove peppers and place on large serving plate.
Peel off blackened skin and carefully remove seeds.
Cut peppers into strips.

title: nut filled cookies
directions: Soften oleo and cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix in flour.
Shape into 24 (1-inch) balls.
Press into tart pans.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Sift together the remaining dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients until thoroughly mixed, but don't overmix.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 55 minutes.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts together until moist. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Allow to cool.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Put hot cooked and drained spinach into a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole dish.
Add cheese and spices and mix well.
Mix crumbs with melted butter and stir 1/2 cup into spinach, then spread other 1/2 cup on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini cake(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar and oil in mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend flour, cinnamon, soda, salt, baking powder and nutmeg in medium bowl.
Stir flour mixture into sugar mixture. Add zucchini, nuts and pineapple.
Stir until well blended. Grease 10-cup plastic or ceramic tube dish.
Coat with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour batter into tube dish.
Cook on level 7 for 20 to 25 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean. Turn quarter turn halfway through cooking time.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Invert on serving platter.

title: 8 layer salad
directions: In a bowl, layer ingredients as listed.
Refrigerate overnight; toss 1 hour before serving.

title: 4th generation sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash potatoes while still hot.
Add butter; mix until all melted.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Brown onion and hamburger until its lost its raw red color. Stir until smooth and add all the other ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: mexican hot chili
directions: Peel and finely dice onions and celery.
Brown in heavy pot with ground beef (drain).
Add seasonings.
Cook together a few minutes.
Add tomato juice and simmer about 1 hour.

title: fruit swirl coffee cake
directions: Generously grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch. Beat sugar, margarine, shortening, baking powder, vanilla, almond extract and eggs in large bowl on low speed.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in flour.
Spread two-thirds of batter in pan.
Spread pie filling over batter. Drop remaining batter by tablespoon onto pie filling.
Bake about 45 minutes or until light brown in 350° oven.
While warm, drizzle with glaze.
Yield:
30 bars.

title: beef or chicken enchiladas
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion and garlic until onion is tender.
Blend in flour.
Stir in broth, milk, chilies, salt and cumin.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Set aside.

title: tortellini and crabmeat salad
directions: This refreshing and light crab salad makes a perfect entree for a luncheon or "covered dish" church supper.
Your budget determines the "degree" of crab in your Crab Louie.
Can be made in smaller portions for a party appetizer.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix well and form into 1 inch balls.
Chill overnight.
Melt 2 1/2 teaspoons Parawax in a double boiler.
Then add 2/3 cup chocolate chips (semi-sweet).
Dip balls in chocolate mix.
Makes approximately 75.

title: lemon-dipped blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg, milk and oil. Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Set aside.
Toss blueberries with 2 tablespoons sugar and lemon rind; fold berries into batter.
Spoon batter into greased or paper lined muffin pans, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Remove from pans and set aside. Combine melted butter and lemon juice.
Dip tops of warm muffins in butter mixture, then sugar.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: one pan turkey and stuffing
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease rectangular baking dish, 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch or 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inches.
Mix baking mix, milk, eggs, parsley, sage, thyme, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper in dish with fork until batter is of uniform color (batter will be lumpy). Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 10-inch dish 35 to 40 minutes; 11-inch dish, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ground beef.
Mix well and add beef.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice; mixing well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add baking powder and milk.
Pour into a deep dish in which oleo is melted.
Pile on fruit.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Using hands or the back of a spoon, cream together the butter and cheese.
Add flour and mix well (the mixture should resemble coarse meal).
Add cayenne and mix on a lightly floured board. Form mixture into two long thin rolls, 1 to 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap each in plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm (about 1 to 2 hours).
Preheat oven to 350°; cut rolls into 1/4-inch slices and arrange on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes until the biscuits are brown around the edges and dry in the middle.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Debone and skin chicken.
Mix cream cheese and chicken with 1 can soup (no water).
Mix 2 cans soup with 1 can broth (may use more).
Spread one tablespoon cheese and chicken mixture on shells and roll.
Layer bottom of square baking dish with soup mixture. Place rolled shells in row.
Pour remaining soup on top.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Cook celery in butter until tender; blend in other ingredients.
Heat and stir often.
Serve over split corn bread squares, biscuits or toast. Serves 3.

title: brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening, sugar, water and vanilla.
Add eggs to creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake 1 sheet at a time for 7 to 9 minutes.
Cookies will appear soft and moist. Do not overbake.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Combine and thoroughly blend the pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar and pumpkin pie spice. Pour into baking pan. Sprinkle the dry cake mix evenly over the top of the pumpkin mixture. Drizzle the melted butter or margarine over the top of the dry cake mix and follow with the pecans (optional). Bake 50 to 60 minutes until the top is golden and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Mix the brown sugar, catsup and barbecue sauce.
Pour over beans; mix well.
Put in a casserole.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole(serves 4 to 6 people)
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Thinly slice apples; put in pie pan.
Sprinkle mix of 1/2 c. sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt on top of apples.
Mix together 1/2 c. sugar, flour and margarine and pat on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° and 40 minutes at 350°.

title: speedy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef, add onion and brown lightly.
Add soups; simmer until well blended.
Serve over rice and chow mein noodles, if desired.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in large pot as they will swell.
Drain. Put fresh water on them.
Add 1 teaspoon soda, 1/2 bacon, 2 onions, salt and pepper.
Cook for 1 hour.
Drain, but save the juice.
In baking dish, put beans, rest of the bacon, onions and brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Add extra juice while baking if they get too dry.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook meat and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup grated cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given and bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 large and 1 small loaf.

title: sock-it-to-me-cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, sour cream and water together.
Place 1/2 in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle 3/4 of the brown sugar and cinnamon on top.
Swirl with a knife.
Place remainder of batter next, then the remainder of the brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Punch holes in sides and top with a knife.
Mix powdered sugar and milk together to make a glaze, then pour over cake.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread in greased pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, until golden brown.
If not brown enough for you, place under broiler for a few minutes; watch carefully.
Cut as desired.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites, and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 - 40 minutes.
Beat egg whites and put on top and brown.

title: lasagne potatoes
directions: Cook noodles to package; drain.
Cut onion into small pieces. In 13 x 9-inch buttered pan, layer noodles on bottom, then potatoes, onion and cheese; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: oven dinner
directions: Brown meat, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in raw potatoes, soup and beans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Mix together salt, oil, vinegar and garlic.
Mash egg yolk and whirl in blender with vinegar mixture.
Combine spinach, onions and mushrooms in 4 salad bowls.
Pour on dressing.

title: minestrone beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
In large kettle, put all ingredients.
Cover and simmer
one
hour.	Serve
as main dish topped with shredded cheese.
Serves 6.

title: delectable chicken
directions: Cook chicken in 425° oven for 20 minutes.
Then spoon half the sauce over chicken and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Turn over and add remaining sauce and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar, salt, and remaining ingredients. Stir to mix well. Pour into freezer and freeze.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Melt honey and butter.
Place popped popcorn and peanuts in a large bowl and mix together.
Spread in a pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: frito salad
directions: Cut up lettuce and tomato.
Add cheese, dressing and Fritos. Mix well and refrigerate until chilled.

title: lo-cal whipped topping
directions: *Fill bowl with crushed ice.
Add water and let set a few minutes.
Drain out amount of water needed.

title: asparagus with bacon
directions: Steam asparagus about 7 minutes. Mix asparagus, parsley, lemon juice and salt. Sprinkle with bacon.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Place on top of potatoes.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pepper green beans
directions: Cook and drain beans.
Saute almonds in 2 tablespoons butter until lightly browned.
Add lemon pepper and toss almond mixture with green beans.

title: soy vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Chill and toss with salad.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain and chop fruits.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add concentrate and stir until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend in Cool Whip and fold in fruit.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold and slice.
Garnish, if desired.
Serves 12.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts, in a pan over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add nuts; spread quickly in buttered dish.
Cool.
Cut in squares.
Yield: 2 dozen pieces.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, milk, egg yolks and vanilla until thick.
Add vanilla wafers and pineapple or banana.

title: barbecue tuna
directions: Cook onion, pepper and celery in water.
Mix tomato juice, sugar, vinegar sauce, mustard, salt and pepper together.
Add to pan and bring to boil.
Add flaked tuna.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until liquid is boiled away.

title: cherry dream squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, 1 cup rolled oats and 6 tablespoons of oleo.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs add egg; mix well.
Press this into prepared pan. Pour cherry pie filling over this crust, spreading to cover.

title: layered green salad(make at least 8 hours ahead)
directions: In long Pyrex dish, layer the first 6 ingredients in order given.
Mix sugar, salt and pepper and sprinkle over mayonnaise. Last, sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over mayonnaise and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Blend in blender; thickens as it cools.

title: dried apple fruitcake
directions: Pour hot water over the raisins; let soak.
Drain well before putting in cake.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Add dried apples and soda.
Add flour and spices.
Add preserves, candied fruit and raisins.
Last, add nuts which have been rolled in flour.
Cook at 275° for 3 hours.
Makes 3 or 4 layers or large tube pan.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender, chop up in small pieces. Use 9x12 pan or smaller.
Spray with pam.
Layer on bottom doritos, chopped chicken, mix soup, rotel and 1 soup can of milk together. Pour over chicken and doritos, sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350 for 30 min.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs, pumpkin and water.
Add flour, soda, salt, baking powder, nutmeg, allspice, cinnamon and cloves.
Add chopped nuts and raisins if desired.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spicy gingerbread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together.
Beat sugar, molasses and shortening into eggs.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add vinegar and water and stir until well blended. Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: lemon curd
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of a double boiler.
Stir well.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
In a large bowl, mix lukewarm water and yeast until the yeast dissolves.
Stir in the warm water and brown sugar.
Slowly add the flour, stirring until the mixture is smooth and does not stick.
Knead on a lightly floured board until it is stretchy and smooth.
Grease 2 cookie sheets and sprinkle with salt or seed.
Pinch off a piece of dough about golf ball size. Roll into a rope about 14 inches long.
Make into a pretzel shape and press ends into dough.
Fill deep frying pan with water.
To each cup of water, add 1 tablespoon of baking soda.
Bring water to a gentle boil.
Use a spatula to dip each pretzel into pan for 30 seconds.
Lift onto cookie sheet and sprinkle with more salt and seed.
Bake 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ziti casserole
directions: Cook ground beef or turkey; drain.
Cook ziti; drain.
Mix together the macaroni, Ricotta cheese, ground beef or turkey and spaghetti sauce.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Serves 8.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, beef, scallions and Worcestershire sauce. Shape into ball or log.
Roll in chopped nuts to cover.
Serve with crackers.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 8-inch glass pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Leave uncovered.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Grease pie plate, sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion over bottom.
Place remainder in blender, blend 1 minute.
Pour into plate.
Bake at 350° in oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: stromboli
directions: Spread dough into rectangle.
Mix together beaten eggs, parsley, garlic powder, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Spread mixture over dough.
Cover with choice of topping.
Roll up like jelly roll and pinch seams together.
Place on cookie sheet in 1/2 moon shape.
Cut even slices halfway through dough 1/2-inch apart. Bake 20 minutes with foil on top.
After 20 minutes, remove foil and bake 10 more minutes.
Cut and serve with hot spaghetti or pizza sauce.

title: coconut delight
directions: Fold together and pour over cool crust.
Reserve toasted coconut for topping.
Let set and chill well.
Spread Cool Whip on top and 1/2 cup toasted coconut.
Keep cool.

title: tortilla "wheels"
directions: Mix all together except tortillas.
Spread equal amount on 10-inch flour tortillas. Roll up tortillas, wrap tightly with plastic wrap and chill.
Slice 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick and serve (discard the end cuts).

title: how to preserve choice children
directions: Mix children and dogs well together.
Put them in a field. Pour over some pebbles.
Sprinkle field with flowers.
Spread over all a blue sky and bake in hot sun.
When brown, remove and set aside to cool in bath tub.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak crosswise in 1/4-inch strips.
(To make slicing easier, you may place steak in freezer for about 30 minutes or until ice crystals begin to form.)
(If desired, slice meat very thin, then tenderizer may not be necessary.)

title: salsa
directions: Cook down to thicken (about 3 hours).
Seal in sterile jars. Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Boil 10 minutes, water, vinegar, sugar and spices (tied in cheesecloth).
Then add peaches.
Cook until mixture blends in thoroughly, about 10 minutes.
Pack peaches in sterilized jars. Fill to top with syrup and seal.

title: hot doggities
directions: Line a 9 x 12-inch cake pan with foil.
Roll hot dogs in catsup or mustard and then in cornflake crumbs.
Arrange in pan so hot
dogs do not touch
each
other.
Bake
at
350°for
30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: mama's yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Heat 2 cups water to boiling and pour over shortening, buttermilk, sugar and salt. Stir until mixture cools.
Add flour, one cup at a time until soft batter is formed.
Add remaining flour and knead until ball becomes smooth and satiny.
Cover with hot damp tea towel and let rise until double in bulk.
Turn out and knead for 2 minutes. Place in 4 greased loaf pans.
Cover and let rise in a warm room. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: eye of round roast
directions: Place roast in rectangular Pyrex (or pan).
Place the bacon on top of the roast.
Secure with toothpicks.
Sprinkle the 5 marinade ingredients on roast and bacon.
Preheat oven to 500°. Turn off oven. Do not open oven door for 2 hours.
Roast will be rare (13 minutes for medium).

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine turkey, egg white and dill weed. Shape into balls, saute until brown in large skillet. Add green pepper and onion to meat and steam 1 minute. Stir in rest of ingredients cover and cook over medium heat about 20 minutes. The macaroni should be tender.

title: oven fried fishgroves, texas
directions: Cut fillets into serving portions.
Combine salt and milk. Dip portions in milk then roll them in dry crumbs.
Place portions in well greased baking dish and drizzle with melted butter. Sprinkle with lemon juice and paprika, if desired.
Place baking dish in pre-heated 500° oven and bake 10 to 12 minutes or until portions flake easily when tested with a fork.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg in bowl and stir in milk and shortening.
Combine dry ingredients and quickly mix with the liquid mixture until the flour is moistened.
Do not overmix; the batter will be lumpy. Fold in blueberries.
Line muffin tins with paper liners and fill each 2/3 full.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from oven and immediately remove from pans to cool.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Combine first six ingredients in a large bowl.
Add 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Place mixture in a baking dish and shape into a loaf.
Combine remaining ingredients in a mixing bowl and pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: phoney abalone
directions: Place chicken between waxed paper and pound thin.
Pour clam juice and garlic over chicken and marinate 36 hours.
Drain chicken and dip in egg, then in flour-bread crumb mixture.
Fry quickly in hot pan with butter or oil.

title: dip
directions: Heat over low flame; mix well.
Use as a vegetable or chip dip.

title: spaghetti with tuna and basil
directions: Heat the olive oil in a large skillet. Add the garlic and crushed red pepper and cook over low heat until the garlic is golden, about 3 minutes. Add the tomatoes and their reserved liquid and simmer over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, about 7 minutes. Add the tuna and simmer briefly to heat through; stir gently to keep the tuna in large pieces. Season with salt and black pepper and keep warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together well and form into balls.
Roll in parsley flakes or chopped nuts.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Add crawfish tails and simmer a while to heat crawfish.
Add soups and seasonings and heat thoroughly.
Serve with rice and French bread.

title: egg pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Add eggs, milk, flavoring, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into shells.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes, or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: pralines #1
directions: Mix sugar, buttermilk, soda and salt.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add oleo and pecans.
Cook until mixture forms a soft ball in water. Remove from heat and beat until creamy.
Drop from spoon on waxed paper.

title: country pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into bottom and side of a 9-inch pie plate.

title: papata
directions: Wash chicken, drain and salt and pepper.
Boil chicken for about 10 minutes.
Remove chicken to cool.
Cook noodles in the broth until tender.
Cut chicken up (into small pieces).

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, milk and butter.
Cook at medium heat until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat to add vanilla.
Beat until it loses its gloss.
Add nuts and pour into buttered dish.

title: never-fail divinity
directions: Combine water, sugar and salt. Bring to rolling boil. Boil for only 2 minutes. Place marshmallow cream in a large bowl and pour hot syrup into it all at once. Stir until candy loses its gloss, then add nuts. Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: paper cup frozen salad
directions: Combine sour
cream,
lemon juice, sugar, salt, pineapple, banana and enough
red food coloring to give a pink tint. Lightly fold in
nuts
and cherries.
Spoon into paper cupcake cups.
Set in muffin tins.
Freeze.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: You can use 3/4 cup molasses instead of sugars.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Keeps well in fridge.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and salt.
Let stand 2 hours; drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Add cucumbers, onion and green pepper.
Put in jar; cover with plastic wrap and rubber band.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy skillet.
Add sugar and water. Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Allow to boil until margarine mixture turns golden brown (hard ball stage).
Remove from heat. Add vanilla.
Stir and then pour into a cookie sheet with sides. Allow to sit for about 5 minutes, then sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Chips will melt.
Spread chocolate.
Sprinkle nuts and allow to cool.
Cut in chunks.

title: louisiana pork chop creole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Remove from pan and saute onion and green pepper in fat.
Place pork chops in pan over onion and pepper. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer slowly over low heat for 50 minutes.
Serve chops and gravy over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Beat egg whites at high speed in a small bowl until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Continue beating until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition.
When meringue is stiff and white, add the rest of the ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls about 1 1/2-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 40 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spread hash browns in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Saute onions in margarine.
Mix with soup, cheese, sour cream and salt.
Pour over hash browns.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Drizzle with margarine, melted.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 12.

title: chowning's tavern brunswick stew
directions: Cut chicken in eight pieces and simmer 2 1/4 hours in 1 gallon of water or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken. Add beans, tomatoes, onions and potatoes to broth.
Simmer until beans are tender, about 1 hour.
Add hot water, if necessary, and stir to prevent scorching. Add corn and chicken, boned and diced,
and seasonings; cook until corn is done. Serves 8 to 10.
Better the day after being prepared.

title: chicken and broccoli skillet
directions: Spray a cold large skillet with nonstick coating.
Preheat skillet over medium heat.
Add broccoli, onion, lemon pepper and thyme to skillet.
Cook and stir for 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Remove vegetable mixture from skillet; keep warm.
Add oil and garlic to hot skillet.
Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Add to skillet.
Cook chicken over medium-high heat 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Return vegetable mixture.
Add cherry tomatoes.
Cover and cook 1 to 2 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: apple or cherry cheese pie
directions: Spread apples or cherries in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Cover with cake mix.
Top with thin slices of margarine.
Add 1 cup of water.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: california beef stew
directions: Put raw meat in baking dish.
Cut up vegetables and add to meat.
Pour soups (undiluted) over the meat and vegetables. Cover lightly and bake 3 hours at 350°.
Delicious!

title: pepper steak
directions: Add enough water to cover meat and cook until the water boils. Add all ingredients, but the vegetables, and cook until meat is tender.
Add the vegetables.
Stir until well blended.
Turn down the heat and simmer until all vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: 2 pecan pies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 2 pie shells at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each egg.
Mix baking powder and flour; add to mixer.
Add milk and vanilla; stir in pineapple.
Pour in cool oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cajun beans and rice
directions: Combine ingredients in crock-pot.
Let cook 4 to 6 hours. Serve over steamed rice.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: First, soften each tortilla in a skillet with a small amount of oil.
Do all of the tortillas before starting the filling. Keep them softened by placing them in a moist kitchen towel.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Mix meat with pizza sauce and other ingredients.
Split the bread lengthwise and spread each with meat.
Broil for 10 minutes. Cover with cheese slices; broil 5 minutes longer until cheese melts.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients listed above.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: "out of this world dessert"
directions: Cook until thick. Approximately 10 minutes in the microwave. Remove from heat. Add 3 oz. dry jello and stir.

Cool completely. Make graham cracker crust for a 9x13 pan or 2 - 9 inch pie plate. Add 4 sliced bananas to the cooled mixture. Pour over graham cracker crust. Add whipped topping and garnish with cherries. Enjoy!

title: pie cherry salad
directions: Dissolve juice of cherries, sugar and jello.
When it comes to a boil, remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water and add to hot mixture.
Add pineapple and juice, orange and lemon rind, salt, nuts and cherries.
Mold.
Serves 10.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix bar ingredients in order given.
Put in a greased jelly-roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, frost.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken enough ahead of time to let it cool so you can pull chicken off bone.
Place half of bread crumbs in baking dish. Pour butter over bread crumbs.
Layer chicken over this.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Add rest of bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Add raisins, dates and nuts, last.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in 4 well-greased and floured loaf pans or 1-pound coffee cans.

title: burger and bow casserole
directions: Cook noodles; pan-fry onions and add beef, salt and pepper. Fry until pink is gone.
Add rest of items and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Mix butter and cookies in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then, with spoon, mix pudding with milk and add soft ice cream, mixing well.
Place on top of crumbs.
Chill for 1 hour.
Put Cool Whip on top and add crushed Heath bars.

title: swedish raisin bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter until creamy and smooth; add eggs and beat well.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add lemon extract, vanilla and milk, along with dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into one large loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) or two small loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake for one hour at 350° or until brown.
Slice very thin when cool.
This is a moist heavy bread with a hint of lemon.
It freezes well.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in melted butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; work in 1 cup of the flour.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix nuts with other cup of flour and fold in.

title: date nut balls
directions: Put in large saucepan margarine, sugar and dates.
Continue to stir until well mixed and a slow boil.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies, pecans and coconut.
Mix well.
Roll in balls in powdered sugar while hot.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: date balls
directions: Combine and boil sugar, butter, eggs, dates and nuts; slowly cook until thickened.
Add cereal and vanilla; drop by teaspoon and roll in coconut.

title: boursin cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with crackers.
Add milk, if not thick.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix Italian dressing according to package.
Chill.
Cook noodles until tender (about 5 minutes).
Cut up red onion and cucumber.
Mix pasta, onion and cucumber.
Chill.
Add dressing before serving.
Be creative.
Add celery, bell peppers, broccoli.

title: heavenly orange fluff
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 1/2 cups of boiling water. Add pineapple and its juice and blend together. Chill until partially set.
Fold in oranges and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: cheesy skillet dinner
directions: Cook beef, onion and mushrooms in large skillet until beef is browned; drain. Stir in salsa and chilies; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 to 3 minutes. Sprinkle with 1 1/2 c. cheese and tortilla chips. Top with remaining cheese. Cover; cook for an additional 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: vegetable cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into a ball and roll in finely chopped pecans.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and add dressing.

title: pineapple cranberry mold
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice; add water to make 1/2 cup. Set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Break up cranberry sauce and add to Jell-O.
Add 1/2 cup of reserved liquid.
Chill until it starts to set.
Add pineapple and apple. Chill until firm.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Mix together and cook first seven ingredients for 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: festive fudge filled bars
directions: Combine oats, flour, nuts, sugar, soda and salt.
Mix well. Add margarine; mix until dry ingredients are thoroughly moistened and mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remaining crumb mix onto bottom of greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: spinach salad with hot bacon dressing
directions: Put spinach in a large salad bowl.
Cook diced bacon in a skillet over moderately high heat until crisp; reduce heat to medium and add sugar, green onions, salt, vinegar, mustard and paprika.
Bring to the boiling point and remove from heat.
Just before serving, pour the hot dressing over the spinach and toss lightly until leaves are coated.

title: charlotte russe
directions: Combine gelatin, 2 tablespoons sugar and skim milk in a small saucepan.
Let stand 1 minute.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in almond extract. Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.

title: cabbage hot dish
directions: Chop cabbage and parboil for 3 minutes; drain.
Brown ground beef and onion, breaking up beef.
Drain well.
Alternate layers of cabbage with meat and onion in 2-quart casserole.
Pour soup on top.
Pierce food with fork several times so soup runs through layers.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mint brownies
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Combine confectioners sugar with extract and enough milk to proper consistency to spread.
Put on cooled cake.
Melt chocolate and butter.
Spread over frosting.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit pizza(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Freeze cookie dough 1 hour.
Slice into 1/8-inch slices.
Line foil lined 14-inch pizza pan with slices, overlapping edges slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Invert onto serving plate and carefully remove foil.
Turn right side up.

title: swiss chard
directions: Wash chard; slit lengthwise and chop.
Bring a pan of water to a boil; cook chard; drain.
Fry bacon; reserve 2 Tbsp. fat. Crumble bacon, set aside.
Dice onion; set aside.
Beat eggs with 2 Tbsp. milk.
Weaken vinegar with water to make 1/2 C. Add to egg mixture and cook till thickened.
Add chard, crumbled bacon, and raw onion.
Serve at once.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Microwave.
Bake potatoes on High, 16 to 17 minutes.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Cut top quarter off of potatoes.
Scoop out the inside.
Reserve shell.
Mash potatoes until smooth.
Beat in butter, sour cream, milk, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Stir in green onions and all but 1/4 cup crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup bacon over top of potato mixture after placing back in shells.
Place on baking sheet. Bake in 400° oven 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: camper's delight salad
directions: Toss vegetables, cheese, mayonnaise and dressing together in a large bowl.
Serve with crackers or as a side dish with any meal.

title: potato and hamburger casserole
directions: Cook
ingredients
until
well done, then put in casserole. Top
with thick layer of mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are brown, or broil 5 to 6 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with celery, carrots, cucumbers, cauliflower and broccoli.

title: mom's home-style vegetable casserole
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, crumble the ground turkey; add onion and microwave on High (100% power), uncovered, for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until cooked through; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, macaroni, water and garlic powder; mix lightly.
Cover with lid and microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes or until almost boiling, stirring once halfway through cooking time.
Mix in vegetables; cover.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes or until macaroni and vegetables are tender; stir twice during cooking time. Stir in cheese and let stand 3 minutes to melt cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet custard creme
directions: Place egg yolks and sugar in a heavy saucepan and whisk together well, about 2 minutes.
Add milk and whisk to blend.
Set the saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the sauce begins to thicken.
Don't allow it to come to a boil or the eggs will curdle!
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into glass or ceramic pitcher and allow to cool.
Serve over fresh fruit, or white cake topped with berries.

title: best ever peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine butter, peanut butter, sugars, vanilla and egg, beating with an electric mixer until fluffy and light.
Stir together the dry ingredients and add to butter mixture using a wooden spoon, blending thoroughly.
Shape into one inch balls and place about 2 inches apart on a baking sheet.
Flatten lightly with fork tines in a criss-cross pattern.
Bake at 325° for about 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: peach crunch
directions: Cut peaches into small bite size pieces.
Use a large cake pan. Empty peaches and syrup into cake pan. Pour dry yellow cake mix on top. Cut butter into small squares to cover top. Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream
butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Mix flour, salt,
soda
and
cream of tartar.
Add eggs to butter mixture; then
gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture. Fold in jam and sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon (or tuna) casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs together.
Put in a loaf pan, sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake in oven.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels in a double broiler or microwave.
Stir in 1/3 cup milk and set aside.
In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, butter and remaining milk; set half aside and press other half into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from the oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips. Pour caramel mixture over; spoon reserved cake mixture on top. Return to oven for 20 minutes.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine corn, pepper, onion, pickle relish and celery in medium heatproof bowl.
Stir together vinegar, oil, sugar, mustard, mustard seed and celery seed in small saucepan.
Bring to boiling; boil 1 minute.
Pour over vegetables; stir well. Refrigerate, covered, overnight; stir occasionally.
Spoon relish in glass jar and tightly cover.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add corn syrup, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: tiramisu
directions: Combine in glass measure the egg yolks, sugar and milk; microwave on High 2 to 4 minutes, stirring with a whisk twice, or just until slightly thickened.
Set in bowl of ice water to cool.

title: north texas state university kerr hall mexican chicken
directions: Mix together onion, American cheese, spices, mashed tomatoes and cream of chicken soup.
Soften tortillas in chicken stock (do not soak too long or they will crumble).
Line long shallow casserole dish with 6 overlapping tortillas.
Cover tortillas with a layer of chicken mixture and another layer of tortillas and chicken mixture.
Heat in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and heat 5 minutes to melt.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts and mix.
Set aside two cups of the mixture for topping.
Press remainder in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Blend sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Add eggs, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread over bottom crust; sprinkle with reserved two cups of topping.
Return to oven and bake for 25 minutes more.
Cool, then chill and cut into 48 pieces.

title: lemon-strawberry punch
directions: Combine lemon peel, lemon juice and 2 1/4 cups strawberries in blender; blend.
In punch bowl, combine sherbet and mixture; stir well.
Pour in soda and stir to blend.
Float lemon cartwheels and strawberry halves in punch.
Makes 10 (8 ounce) servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs.
Add bread cubes, V-8 juice, thyme, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add meat, onion and bell pepper; mix well. Shape into loaf; cover with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice dinner
directions: Brown rice with oil.
Add water.
Add tomato, onion and green pepper.
Add Treet meat or bouillon cubes.
Add tomato sauce. Cook about 1 hour.
Set aside.
When rice gets thick, ready to eat.

title: nacho dip texas style
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add remaining ingredients. Heat thoroughly and serve with tortilla chips.

title: martha's chocolate cake
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over Step #2.

title: broccoli cheese quiche
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on box.
Mix soup, egg and cheese; add this to broccoli.
Pour mixture into room temperature pie crust.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: gravy
directions: Need gravy without the calories?
Cook the cauliflower as directed with the bouillon cube.
Drain.
Put in a blender and blend until gravy consistency.
Use as a gravy or eat alone.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine drink powder, tea powder, ground cinnamon, sugar and cloves.
Store in sealed container for up to 4 months.
Makes 2 cups mix (enough for 12 servings).

title: beef and veggies
directions: Cut steak into strips (bite size) and marinate in cooking sherry, teriyaki sauce, soy sauce, sugar and garlic (finely chopped) for 2 hours.

title: favorite cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add the next 7 ingredients. Sift remaining ingredients together.
Add to mixture.
Mix all well.
Bake in ungreased cookie sheet.
Allow to cool slightly before removing.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Don't overbake. Yield:
3 dozen.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directions on box. Add can of condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Arrange layers of bananas and vanilla wafers in bowl.
Pour pudding mix over each layer.
Top with vanilla wafers.

title: baked lemon pudding
directions: Cream
the butter and sugar.
Add the lemon rind, lemon juice, egg
yolks,
flour
and
milk.
Stir in the beaten egg whites. Bake in a baking dish or custard cups in a pan of hot water in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: crab enchiladas
directions: In a large baking pan, place a tortilla at one end.
Fill across center with crab meat and cheese.
Sprinkle with olives and chiles to your taste.
Roll tortilla into itself, forming a roll. Repeat process until pan is full.
Sprinkle a thin layer of cheese over the top.
Sprinkle with olives and chiles.
Pour cream over tortillas.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until tortillas start to brown.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Drain half of the juice from the peaches; spread peaches in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Melt butter and dribble over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool before serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: Pour tomato juice in large pot.
Add rice; dice and cook onion and bell pepper in margarine until tender.
Add hamburger when rice is done and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve with nachos and cheese.

title: robin's french dressing
directions: Process in blender until liquified.
To make a low calorie version, use 1/2 cup canola oil and 1 cup vinegar and Equal to taste instead of sugar.

title: face paint
directions: In each cup of a muffin tin, mix ingredients, a different color for each cup.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook and stir wild rice, celery and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Pour into ungreased casserole.
Heat broth to boiling.
Pour over rice and add mushrooms and salt to taste. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Spread each side of chop with thin layer of mustard.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Coat with flour.
Fry in hot oil.
After browning on both sides, lower skillet to simmer.
Mix soup with 1 can of water.
Pour over chops and simmer until tender.
May be served over rice.

title: peach pie supreme
directions: Peel peaches; slice them.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake in a 9-inch pie crust (raw) for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: peppermint pie
directions: Early in the day, mix crushed chocolate wafers with melted butter; press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate. Refrigerate.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichokes.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes (until brown on top).
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well and add flour and cinnamon. Mix well and add (fold with spoon, do not overmix) the apples and pecans.
Bake in 3 layers for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per directions.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put a layer of coconut, then a layer of pecans.
Pour in cake batter.
Mix together powdered sugar, melted butter and cream cheese.
Drop spoonfuls of mixture through cake without getting on the sides.
Bake 15 minutes longer than the cake box says.

title: apricot delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add juices and fruit. Pour into 9 x 13 dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Let set.

title: praline pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, granulated sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Add pumpkin and cream; mix well.
Pour into pie shell; cover edge with foil.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil.
Melt butter and add remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle nut mixture over pie.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.

title: stuffed chicken custard
directions: Beat milk, eggs, nutmeg, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning together.
Place chicken stuffing, chicken and peas in greased casserole.
Pour beaten egg mixture over stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Reserve drippings.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Set aside.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Spoon batter into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool; remove from pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew chicken in water with celery and onion to taste.
Debone; cut chicken into small bite size pieces.
Cover and set aside. Boil vermicelli in chicken broth until just done; drain and save broth.
Place mushroom soup, tomatoes, tomato soup and cheese in boiler and heat slowly to liquify.
Add chicken, vermicelli, chestnuts and mushrooms; stir lightly.
If mixture appears to be too dry, a small amount of broth may be added.
Bake at 350° only until it bubbles, as it can be easily overcooked.
Cheese may be placed on top of casserole if desired, but I like mine mixed into the casserole.

title: shrimp stew
directions: Saute
onions
in
hot bacon drippings 10 minutes.
Add tomato paste, 5 cups water, pepper, thyme, bay leaf and salt. Bring
to boil and add shrimp.
Cook 15 minutes.
Cover kettle or
pot
and cook over low fire about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over steamed rice. Sprinkle lightly with gumbo file.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, pineapple, sugar, marshmallows and nuts. Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, add whipped cream and chill again.
This recipe will serve 8 people.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Combine pudding, sugar,
milk and margarine in a saucepan. Cook over
medium-high
heat,
stirring constantly until mixture comes to a full
boil.
Lower heat and boil slowly for 3 minutes, stirring
constantly.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in peanuts.
Beat
until
candy
thickens
(about 15 minutes).
Drop quickly
from
teaspoon
onto waxed paper forming clusters.
Makes about 24 clusters.

title: blueberry icebox cake
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and melted butter and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan, well buttered.
Blend eggs with sugar and cream cheese.
(Do with mixer for best results.)
Spread over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Pour on pie mix.
Any kind of pie mix may be used.
Top with Cool Whip. Keep in refrigerator until serving time.
Cut in squares.
(Will keep several days if covered in refrigerator.)

title: grandma's rolls
directions: Dissolve 1 teaspoon
sugar and yeast in lukewarm water. Scald milk; add to sugar, salt and shortening in a large bowl. Beat in 3 cups flour.
When
mixture is not too hot for yeast, add yeast and eggs;
then add 3 more cups of flour.
Let stand 1 hour.
Knead; let
stand
until
double in bulk.
Then work into small balls (large
walnut-size
or
larger
if
you want large rolls).
Let stand,
covered,
in
a
warm
place
until light.
Bake at 350° for
minutes.
Makes 5 dozen small to medium rolls.
You can use
water
and 1/2 cup powdered milk; mix with sugar.
You might like
to
take a stick of oleo and rub over tops when baked.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Peel peaches and leave whole.
Bring to boil the sugar, cinnamon, cloves, water and vinegar.
Boil 2 or 3 minutes; add the peaches and cook a few minutes until the peaches are tender.
Put peaches in sterilized jars.
Fill with the liquid and seal.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Roll thin and bake in hot oven about 15 minutes or until they get a little brown. These are real good.

title: cheese soup
directions: Bring to boil the cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, potatoes and onion in 1 quart of water.
Stir occasionally.
Add bouillon cubes.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add soup and cheese.
Simmer until cheese is melted.

title: horseradish cheese balls
directions: Beat the cheese until smooth, may have to add 2 to 3 tablespoons milk to reach smooth stage.
Add horseradish and seasonings, then the beef and mix well.
Shape into balls and refrigerate until very firm.
Take from refrigerator and roll balls in fresh parsley.
Return to refrigerator and chill again.

title: bananas on the grill
directions: Carefully slice each banana lengthwise without cutting the bottom peel.
Spread apart lightly.
Sprinkle each banana with 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
Wrap each tightly in double fold of foil. Grill on "Medium" flame setting of gas grill with hood closed for 15 minutes or until warm.
Turn several times during cooking period.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding enough sweet milk to mix thoroughly, but not too loosely.
Cook in a large skillet in oven set on 400° until done.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix creamed cottage cheese, parmesan cheese, browned ground beef, egg and parsley flakes.
Layer noodles, ground beef mixture, mozzarella cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Makes 2 layers.

title: chicken a la creole
directions: Cook chicken until meat falls from bone.
Take liquid which should be 1 quart or more and add celery, peppers and onions. Cook until tender.
Add diced chicken, salt, Worcestershire sauce, pimentos, mushrooms and cheese.
Allow to age in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.
Bake slow in oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.
Freezes well and is most convenient for last minute unexpected guests.

title: bunsteads
directions: Mix together.
Put in hot dog buns (6 to 8).
Wrap in foil and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: date and walnut cake
directions: Rub fat into flour.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix with the milk.
Bake in an 8-inch cake tin at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer sauerkraut, corned beef and 2 cups Swiss cheese in 13 x 9 baking dish. Mix mayo and dressing and pour over ingredients in dish. Sprinkle remaining 2 cups cheese. Mix butter and bread crumbs and sprinkle over top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and drain 1 hour.
Combine cranberries and sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain again.
Combine next 3 ingredients with drained cranberries.
Fold in whipped cream. Chill.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken or shrimp pasta
directions: In a skillet saute onion, mushrooms, and peppers together. Add shrimp, crawfish or chicken to skillet; saute until tender. Cook the pasta according to directions on pkg.
Drain.
Then mix all ingredients into a casserole baking dish.
Layer cheese on top.
Bake for
20 to 30 minutes at 350° covered.
Serves 10.

title: rosie's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Enjoy.
It's great.

title: milk punch
directions: In mixer, blend together the softened ice cream and milk.
Add bourbon and mix.
Place mixture in freezer until ready to use. The mixture fits conveniently into two 1/2-gallon milk cartons. Take from freezer and place in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Do not thaw completely; leave icy.
Serve from silver pitcher.
Makes approximately 1 gallon.

title: cowboy biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients, mix well.
Work into a ball and let rise.
Roll out.
Cut into biscuits and bake at 400°.
Can be refrigerated for several days.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix flour and meal together. Add salt and paprika. Slice tomatoes, sprinkle with salt. Slightly beat egg, dip tomato slices in egg, dredge in flour mixture. Fry in hot oil.

title: mom's brown sugar squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9-inch square pan over low heat.
Beat eggs slightly.
Combine sugar, flour, soda and nuts and stir into beaten eggs.
Then add vanilla.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir!
Bake for 20 minutes.
Turn out of pan.
When cool, cut into squares and dust bottoms with confectioners sugar.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put bread on the bottom of 9 x 13 in. pan.
Crumble bacon and sausage on top of the bread.
Sprinkle cheese on top of the meat. Pour eggs on top of the cheese.
Cover and let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Cook at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Combine other ingredients, except biscuits. Mix in browned, drained meat and onions.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese in bowl.
Add onions and shredded cheese and mix well.
Sprinkle with paprika and garlic salt; season to taste and mix well again.
Roll mixture into a round ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and combine with peanut butter.
Mix well, adding confectioners sugar and milk alternately.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put mixture in graham cracker crust and top with chopped, salted peanuts.
Wrap and freeze.

title: chile con queso
directions: Melt both cheeses together on low heat or use low heat of an electric fondue pot. After cheeses melt, add evaporated milk, stirring constantly. Add remaining ingredients. Stir to blend flavors.
Add more evaporated milk if mixture becomes too thick. Serve warm in electric skillet, fondue pot or chafing dish with tortilla chips.

title: strawberry lemonade
directions: Combine first three ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Pour into a larger pitcher.
Stir in cold water, ice and, if desired, lemon slices.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli.
Saute onion in small amount of chicken broth. Mix together and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, the chicken broth, gravy mix, milk and cornstarch.
Reduce heat, add in cheeses.
Add onions and cooked broccoli.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: maine's melt-in-your-mouth blueberry cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg yolks.
Sift dry ingredients three times.
Beat egg whites stiff and set aside.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately to egg yolk/sugar mixture. Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Fold in blueberries.
Spread batter in 9 x 9-inch greased pan and sprinkle lightly with sugar. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hot scrod
directions: Cut fish into bite-sized pieces and marinate in dressing 2 hours.
Add celery and mushrooms to fish.
Mix mayonnaise, milk and grated cheese.
Combine all ingredients, except crackers.
Place in casserole.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: parkerhouse rolls
directions: Combine yeast and warm water in a 2-cup liquid measuring cup; let stand 5 minutes. Combine 4 cups sifted flour, sugar and salt in a large bowl. Stir in yeast mixture and shortening. Add eggs and remaining 1 cup sifted flour; stir vigorously until well blended. (Dough will be soft and sticky.) Brush or lightly rub dough with some of the melted butter. Cover loosely; let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils; place in large kettle with salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Add ham; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer gently. One hour later, add vegetables.
Simmer one hour until done.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In a blender, mix the sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar together.
Add onion juice and blend well.
Add oil slowly with blender on and continue to blend until thick.
Add poppy seed and blend for a few seconds.
Use at once or store in refrigerator. If chilled, allow to warm to room temperature before using.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch pieces.
Coat a large skillet with cooking spray.
Add meat and cook until browned.
Add next 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add green pepper, cover and simmer for 10 more minutes.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and lemon flavoring.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 250° or longer if needed.

title: apple cake with topping
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well, then stir in apples.
Put in 9 x 13 pan. Add topping.
Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.

title: fresh fruit cobbler
directions: Mix together in pan the 2/3 to 1 cup sugar and cornstarch; stir in gradually the boiling water.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add fresh fruit (juice and all).
Pour into an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Dot with a little butter; sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Mix other ingredients in the order listed; drop by spoonful onto fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on broiler pan.

title: hot cocoa
directions: In a saucepan, combine cocoa, sugar and water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add milk.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil. Pour into mugs and top with marshmallows or marshmallow cream.

title: never fail pie meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and water in small saucepan.
Cook until thick and clear, about 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool. Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add flavoring and cornstarch, mix and beat until fluffy and is peaking.

title: brown eyed susans
directions: Mix all ingredients except stars.
Roll into small balls, about 1-inch.
Top with a chocolate star.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 350° or on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup of the cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can French fired onions. Pour into a 1-quart casserole. Bake, covered, for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Add the other ingredients in the order given.
Simmer 4 to 5 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tortellini rapid
directions: Cook tortellini as per package directions.
While cooking, saute garlic in small amount of olive oil.
Add peas and mushrooms. Cook until tender.
Drain tortellini.
Toss with peas and serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour 3 times.
Cream margarine, sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flavoring.
Add flour, salt and baking powder (mixed together) alternately with milk.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: wilted bacon salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a small suacepan and bring to a boil.
Simmer uncovered for 5 minutes, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Place salad greens in a large bowl and pour vinegar mixture over greens, tossing gently.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese. Put in a buttered casserole; top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cooked cabbage with meat juice
directions: The day before, make a pork roast; drain and save juice. Put in refrigerator overnight. Skim off fat from juice and put in pan; heat. Cut cabbage in pieces and cook until done.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water. Blend in other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add water and oil.
Mix and knead until you are able to roll into a smooth ball.
Place in warm place with towel over it.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Punch down and let set for 4 minutes.
Roll out and place on pan and let rise for 15 minutes.
Add toppings (sauce, cheese, meats, veggies, etc.). Place pizza in cold oven, set temperature to 500° and bake for 15 to 17 minutes, or longer depending on your oven!
(This recipe works best on "Air-Pans.")

title: chicken manicotti
directions: Boil chicken until done; mince chicken. Cook manicotti shells.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add milk and water.
Mix well. Bring to a boil.
Cook until a ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Separate egg whites from yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add yolks and continue beating until stiff.
Pour hot Chocolate Sauce over eggs and stir well.
Serve over warm biscuits!

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together the same as pie crust.
Take out 1 cup crumbs and reserve.
Add the sour milk and baking soda to remaining crumbs.
Mix well.
Put in greased pan (8 x 10-inch) or something similar.
Sprinkle crumbs over the top and bake in a moderate oven 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: brown oatmeal rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; cool to lukewarm.
Add shortening and yeast, softened in the lukewarm water.
Add brown sugar and salt and beat in enough flour to knead.
Knead about 10 minutes.
Let rise until double; punch down and make rolls or bread and let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes for rolls; 350° for 50 to 60 minutes for bread.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread in bowl. Mix all ingredients in with cornbread and stir. Refrigerate to chill.

title: angel flake biscuit
directions: Dissolve
yeast in warm water.	Stir yeast mixture into room temperature buttermilk; mix well and set aside.
Combine flour and
sugar;
cut
in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk mix.	Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.	You
may
cover
and refrigerate at this time. If you plan
to
use immediately, cover with towel.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch
dough down; turn out on lightly floured surface; knead
lightly
3 to 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness; cut
with
to
inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased
baking
sheet.
Bake
at
for
10 to 20 minutes.

title: jiffy cobbler(peach, blueberry)
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 8-inch square casserole dish. Stir flour, sugar and milk together until just blended.
Spoon carefully over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour the sweetened fruit over the batter.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve warm with whipped topping or vanilla ice cream.
Makes 6 good servings.

title: mini cheese tarts
directions: Whip cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend together thoroughly.
Place one vanilla wafer in bottom of each cupcake liner.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: tomato cocktail
directions: Scald and skin the tomatoes. Cut into quarters or smaller.
To this, add the remaining ingredients. Cook until soft enough to run through colander.
Reheat and put in jars.
Cook to seal.

title: best cake
directions: Mix by hand; will be lumpy.
Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl add pineapple and fruit cocktail (juice and all).
Then drain the oranges and add.
Now add pudding and stir well.
Add the grapes and cherries just before serving. Refrigerate for about 6 hours before serving.
Any fruit can be added.

title: apple bread
directions: In a bowl, combine dry ingredients, pecans and currants.
Add oil, eggs, vanilla and rum extract.
Stir just to blend.
Fold in apples and orange peel.
Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Decorate top with pecans and orange peel.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes until toothpick comes out clean. Cool; refrigerate.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale, together well.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Use the flavor of Kool-Aid according to the color of punch you want.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, eggs, oatmeal (enough to work together), garlic and onion salt. Make out into small meatballs. Fry until brown. Place in crock-pot. Pour pizza sauce and soup over meatballs. Cook on low heat for 1 hour.
Add hickory smoked barbecue sauce and cook until ready to eat.

title: rickey's crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth. Pick shells out of crab meat. Add all other ingredients; mix thoroughly. Refrigerate for couple of hours to mix flavors.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: Cream together cheese and pudding mix.
Gradually add milk and beat until smooth.
If necessary, add additional milk until mixture is the consistency of a thick sauce.
Add flavoring to taste, then fold in whipped topping.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Sear steak in metal soup pot.
Bake in oven at 350° until dry (1 hour).
Remove steak and add a little water to make stock.
It should be rich dark brown.

title: brown sugar squares
directions: Mix and spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into squares.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Boil breasts until tender.
Remove meat and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Mix into chicken.
Make Stove Top mix as directed.
Drop stuffing onto chicken mixture.
Spread evenly.
Cover and bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Slice chicken breast to make a pocket.
Add seasoning, mustard, ham and cheese in the pocket, cover and dredge in bread crumbs. Spray baking dish with cooking spray.
Place chicken in dish, cover with foil and bake 30 minutes to 1 hour, depending how many or how big your chicken breast is.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil sliced potatoes with sliced onion.
Butter casserole dish.
Place 1/2 the drained potatoes in pan.
Add soup, evaporated milk, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Layer with slices of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas pecan pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Mix thoroughly and add to an unbaked 9-inch pastry shell. Cook for 1 hour at 325°.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, salt, vanilla and egg.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Spread in bottom of pie crust. Sprinkle with pecans.

title: ginger freeze (raspberry or strawberry)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender, cover and process until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yields 2 cups.

title: chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter (reserve 1 tablespoon butter) until smooth.
Add chicken, milk, salt, pepper, onion and pepper.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles, firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto dough.
Pull 4 corners up to top and twist and seal edges. Brush tops with reserved butter; sprinkle crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stack cake
directions: Cream sorghum and butter until well blended. Combine milk with beaten eggs. Mix together. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture. Stir only until smooth. Divide in 6 parts, 1 cup each. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Put together with cooked, dried apples or apple butter.

title: taco dip
directions: In a crock-pot or double boiler, combine all ingredients.
Cook about one hour on low heat or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spoon bread
directions: To boiling water, add salt and cornmeal, stirring constantly. Cook to soft mush.
Cool.
Add egg yolks, butter and baking powder.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in buttered baking dish for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot.

title: baked chicken and cheese
directions: Place chicken breast in a buttered 9 x 13 baking dish and top each piece with a slice of cheese.
Mix together soup, milk and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and top with stuffing mix.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes, remove foil and bake an additional 30 - 40 minutes.

title: chewy macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 large cookie sheets.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Drain blackberries, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Dredge blackberries in 1/2 cup flour.
Combine butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl, beating well after each addition.
Combine 2 1/2 cups flour, cocoa, soda and spices. Add to creamed mixture alternately with blackberry juice, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in blackberries and vanilla.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Mix well.
Put in microwave dish and cook on High for 7 minutes. Rotate dish 1/4 turn after 3 minutes.

title: reunion scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in buttered baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan over low heat, until blended and cheese is melted.
Pour over potatoes and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shredded pork sandwiches
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Top with onions and all other ingredients.
Cook 8 to 10 hours on low setting.
Remove roast from crock-pot and shred (removing fat).

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes, chill and grate. Melt margarine and cheese. Add onions, sour cream and milk. Combine sauce with grated potatoes. Season to taste. Bake in a greased baking dish for 45 minutes at 325°. Serves 12.

title: joyce's tortilla pie
directions: Brown meat with bell pepper, onion, garlic salt and pepper in a large pot or wok; drain off excess fat.
Add soup and water; mix well.
Spray or grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place a layer of tortilla chips in bottom of pan.
Pour on some of the meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with additional chopped onion and cheese.
Cover with foil and bake for about 1 hour or until bubbly in a 350° oven.
