title: no peek chicken
directions: Spread rice on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt margarine with the 1/2 cup of milk and pour over rice.
Place pieces of chicken on top of the rice (I take the skin off).
Combine your creamed soups with the can of milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle the packet of onion soup over the chicken.
Cover the pan with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
No peek!

title: bourbon blizzard
directions: Combine 2 cups ice milk, 2 cups milk, bourbon, vanilla and nutmeg in container of an electric blender.
Process until smooth. Pour into a large bowl.
Add 1/3 each of remaining ice milk and milk to blender.
Process until smooth.
Add to bowl.
Repeat procedure twice with remaining ice milk and milk.
Stir with a wire whisk to blend.
Cover and chill.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix soup and gelatine.
Add water; heat until smooth and hot. Add cream cheese and blend well, then add celery, mayo, onion and shrimp.
Spray mold with Pam; put mixture in mold and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tiny ham-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Thinly slice tops from cherry tomatoes; remove pulp.
Drain shells upside-down on paper towels.
In small bowl, combine ham, sour cream and horseradish.
Fill the tomato shells with the ham mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Beat together eggs, sugar mixture, milk and softened butter.
Pour in pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sassafras rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except milk. Place in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish and pour milk around the sides of the dish.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until brown at edges.
May top with cayenne or paprika to taste.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Blend milk, eggs, cornstarch and mayonnaise until smooth. Stir in meat, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Turn into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Gradually add to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Stir in juices and orange rind.
Chill until set.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put margarine in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Melt in oven.
Remove. In a large bowl, combine beaten eggs, flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add cheese and spinach.
Mix well.
Spoon into pan and level off.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes. Cool 45 minutes before cutting.

title: italian coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, oil, and egg yokes together.
Add vanilla, flour, baking soda, and salt.
Add coconut.
Add Pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in batter.
Bake in 3 layers or 9 x 13 inch pan at 375 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: polskie krusciki(angel wings)
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Beat well.
Add brandy and cream of tartar. Beat well.
Add flour until dough doesn't stick to hands.
Roll very thin and cut into pieces 3 x 1-inches.
Slit each piece in the center and pull one end through.
Fry in hot oil until lightly brown.
Turn once.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cook and drain ground beef and sausage.
Mix with water and cornstarch.
Take wrapper and lay diagonal.
Put paste on 3 corners.
Put 2 tablespoons of ingredients in center and fold bottom corner up first.
Roll tightly.
Deep-fry until crisp. Freezes well.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: apple cinnamon cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 9 in. round or square baking pan. Reserve 1 cup muffin mix. Pour remaining mix into a bowl, add 1/2 cup milk and stir. Spread into prepared pan. Spoon apple pie filling over the top. Pour reserved muffin mix into a bowl and add softened butter. Blend until crumbly. Sprinkle over pie filling. Top with chopped nuts if desired. Bake 40 minutes or until top is golden brown. Delicious when topped with ice cream.

title: swiss steak
directions: Flour and fry cubed steak until almost done.
Drain and put in casserole dish.
In a separate bowl, combine tomato paste, water, chili sauce, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over steaks and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: butterscotch-peanut krispies
directions: Combine margarine with butterscotch chips in large microwavable bowl. Microwave on High until melted, about 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir. Add marshmallows and microwave on High until melted, about 2 minutes. Stir in cereal and peanuts and press into 8 x 12-inch glass dish.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and lemon.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Beat with electric mixer.
Add nuts.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool in pan briefly; pour over it the juice of lemon with 1/3 cup sugar that has been dissolved. Allow to cool in pan.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix everything but cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put cheese on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done; cut up and save stock.
Grease casserole dish and place chicken in bottom.
Cover with broccoli. Mix chicken soup with 1 cup of chicken stock, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle dressing over all.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2
x
2 1/2-inch loaf pan and set aside. Heat oven to moderate
Put eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in large bowl,
with
electric mixer; beat until light and fluffy. Add sour
cream, flour, cinnamon, soda and baking powder;
beat well.
Fold
in crushed strawberries.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 55 to	60
minutes
or
until	bread tests done.

title: shrimp soup
directions: In pot at low setting, blend potato soup and milk.
Add beef and tomato soups.
Let cook 6 to 8 hours.
One hour before serving, add shrimp.
Immediately prior to serving, sprinkle with basil leaves.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until barely tender.
Combine all ingredients except for the green pepper and onion in blender.
Pour the ingredients over carrots, green pepper and onion.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: irish nut bread
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients, add remaining ingredients. Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Place
in 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 13-inch glass pan.
While still warm, punch holes in cake by inserting a fork and pulling back.
Fill the holes with the condensed milk and cream of coconut, mixed together.
As you pull fork back, pour approximately 2 tablespoons of the mixture into the holes.
For best results, make holes close together. After you have filled the holes, if any of the mixture is left, pour it over the top.
Chill the cake.
Spread with the carton of Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: sugar-free fudge
directions: Melt margarine over low heat. Add chocolate and stir just until melted. Remove from heat. Stir in sweetener and vanilla. Combine chocolate mixture with cream cheese and beat until smooth. Stir in the nuts and spread mixture in a lightly greased 8-inch square pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 64 squares.

title: bubbling jade punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in cold water, lemonade concentrate and pineapple juice.
Chill well.
Pour mixture into bowl.
Add ginger ale.
(Optional:
Garnish with strawberries.) Yield:
Approximately 10 cups.

title: grandpa's favorite grilled bratwurst and mustard cabbage
directions: Place cabbage, 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon salt in a large saucepan.
Cook, covered, over medium heat, for 15 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Mix Stove Top and margarine (melted) together and put 1/2 in bottom of a dish.
Mix chopped chicken, sour cream and chicken soup (undiluted) together.
Put on top of Stove Top mix, then put on remaining Stove Top mix.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Combine syrup and rum.
Pour over reserved cherries and refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix together the sugars and flour.
Beat thoroughly the eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Add to sugar mixture.
Fold in pecans. Pour into an 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: main dish salad
directions: Mix ingredients in large serving bowl.
Serve with salad dressing of choice and salad crackers.

title: grammie b's cheese soup
directions: Cook
celery,
carrots and onions in water and bouillon about 20	minutes or until tender.
Add chicken broth, cauliflower and broccoli.
Cook about 10 more minutes. Add soup and cheeses. Heat,
but	do not boil.
Turkey, chicken or ham can be added. Serves 20.

title: patio potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Place in well greased casserole and sprinkle with chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry; stir until well blended. Pour over the waiting casserole; top with bread crumbs, cheese and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab bisque
directions: Blend soups.
Stir in milk and cream; heat just to boiling. Add crab meat; heat through.
Add cooking sherry just before serving.
Float butter on top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa 5 minutes after it comes to boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until thick.
Pour in buttered plates and cut into squares.

title: crunchy sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork into bite-size squares. Brown in own fat. Add water. Cover and simmer until pork is tender. Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, vinegar, juice and soy sauce. Cook 10 minutes. Pour sauce over pork; let stand 30 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and cook 3 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Peel onions.
Place, root side down, in small glass dish.
Top each onion with a sprinkle of bouillon, a dash of Worcestershire sauce and 1 teaspoon butter.
Cover dish with plastic wrap, leaving 1 corner open.
Bake in microwave for 3 to 5 minutes on 100% power (High).

title: cranberry orange salad
directions: Add pineapple, orange juice, sugar, and nuts to cranberries. Dissolve Jello in water and cool.
Combine all ingredients, place in mold and chill overnight.

title: oyster cracker mix
directions: Place
crackers
in
large
mixing
bowl.
Mix	oil and spices well and pour over crackers.
Stir, making sure crackers are covered with oil and spices.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake
45 minutes in a 225° oven.
Stir occasionally while baking.

title: oxtail stew
directions: Season oxtails using garlic/onion powder in 4-quart pot.
Boil meat at medium-low temperature for 1 1/2 hours.
Add onion, vegetables and more seasoning (your taste).
Once vegetables have been added, cover pot and let it come to a boil.
After it reaches boiling point, lower heat to medium low setting and continue to cook for an additional 1 1/2 hours until vegetables are tender.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll into small balls, then roll balls in mixture of 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375°.
Do not overbake.
Take out before cookies get brown, 8 to 10 minutes approximately.

title: paska(slovak easter bread)
directions: Add shortening to hot milk, then add sugar.
Dissolve and cool to lukewarm.
Add crumbled yeast; stir in eggs and add flour and raisins.
Knead well (about 20 minutes), until smooth and elastic. Dough should be lighter than for bread.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.
After it has risen for the second time, put dough on board and let rest for 10 minutes.
Form into round loaf to fit a 2-quart greased casserole or pan.
Let rise for about 45 minutes, or until double in size.
Top can be decorated with a cross made of strips of dough, braided and each end of braid pressed firmly into dough.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fun cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream butter or shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture slowly. Stir in M&M's and nuts.

title: asparagus chinese style
directions: Put asparagus in a large, shallow skillet; pour in boiling water.
Return to a boil and cook 5 minutes only; drain thoroughly and chill.
Toss with marinade not more than 1/2 hour before serving or it will turn asparagus dark.
Good for company as can be made 1 or 2 days ahead and served cold or at room temperature.

title: maple pecan pie
directions: Place rack in lowest position in oven.
Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: ribbon raspberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add raspberries.
Stir until thawed. Add pineapple and banana.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into clear glass bowl.
(Do not refrigerate remaining mixture.) Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Spread sour cream over chilled jello mixture. Pour remaining mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: baked stuffed carrots
directions: Place carrots in a skillet; add 1-inch water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain. Cut a thin lengthwise slice out of each carrot. Scoop out carrot, leaving a 1/4-inch shell; set aside. Process the removed carrot in a blender until finely chopped. Transfer to a bowl; add mayonnaise, onion, horseradish, nutmeg, salt and pepper. Spoon into carrot shells. Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all together and chill several hours before serving.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; add 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter and roll in flour.
Fry in melted shortening until browned on all sides.
Remove from pan.
Pour bouillon into pan.
Mix 2 tablespoons of flour and water to a smooth paste and add, stirring until thickened.
Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper.
Add meatballs and simmer 20 minutes. Serve hot over buttered noodles or alone.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, milk and margarine in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil; boil for 90 seconds. Remove from heat. Add uncooked oats, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Saute vegetables in melted butter until tender.
Add chicken and seasonings.
Add cream cheese to mixture and blend over low heat until cheese is melted.
Pour mixture into buttered casserole and heat in oven at 350° until top is golden brown.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in strips.
Combine flour, salt and pepper and coat meat.
Cook meat in hot oil until browned on both sides.
Drain tomatoes and reserve liquid.
Add tomato liquid, water, onion, garlic and gravy base.
Cover and simmer about 1 1/4 hours until meat is tender.

title: sweet-sour slaw with kidney beans
directions: Combine beans, cabbage, pickles, onions and raisins; mix. Combine chile sauce, mayonnaise and celery seed for dressing.
Pour over salad and mix to coat evenly.
Serves 6.

title: coleslaw
directions: Remove any wilted outer leaves from cabbage.
Cut into quarters and remove tough center.
Wash under cold running water.
Drain well and dry with paper towels.
Grate on a vegetable shredder or the coarsest side of a regular grater.
Peel and finely chop onion. Wash and dry parsley.
Snip into small pieces with kitchen scissors.
Mix all ingredients together with a fork.
Put in a cold place until ready to serve.

title: squash puffs
directions: Mix and drop by spoonfuls into deep fryer until golden brown.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover 11 x 15-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Slice bananas over crumbs.
Slice ice cream 1/2-inch thick and place slices over bananas.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Place in freezer until firm.
Melt butter and chocolate chips over low heat.
Add sugar and milk and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool and pour over crumb mixture.
Chill.
Add 1/4 cup powdered sugar and vanilla to Cool Whip.
Pour over all.
Freeze.
Serve in slices or squares. Serves approximately 25.

title: raisin bran muffins(cypress inn recipe)
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla. Sift flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon. Add buttermilk and fold in box of Raisin Bran until dissolved. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Place on middle rack; do not overcook.
Grease pans with Pam generously. These will come out perfect and delicious.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Put butter in baking dish to melt.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add milk all at once.
Stir to blend.
Spread butter over bottom of pan.
Add 1/2 of batter.
Arrange peaches over the batter.
Pour on the rest of batter.
Bake 45 minutes or until brown.
Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt; then mix with 3/4 cup of the cheese (reserving other 1/4 cup of cheese.)
Mix the egg, shortening and milk together and then stir egg mixture into cheese mixture with a fork.
Spoon into greased muffin pans (about 2/3 full) and sprinkle with remaining 1/3 cheese.
Bake in 425° oven for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: skinny potato scallop(low calorie)
directions: In nonstick 9-inch square baking pan, combine mushrooms, potatoes and onion.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add salt, thyme and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.
About 55 calories each.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Let cool; cut into chunks.
Mix with soup and milk.
Cook 15 minutes.
Melt margarine; mix with dressing.
Put half dressing in casserole dish.
Layer with chicken.
Put rest of dressing on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, crumble and set aside.
Reserve 2 teaspoons bacon drippings in saucepan.
Discard remainder.
Add onion to saucepan and cook until lightly browned.
Add diced potatoes and water; cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add corn, milk, salt and pepper; heat through (do not boil).
Top each serving with crumbled bacon.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients together.
Heat in saucepan until cheese and butter are melted.
Spread onto English muffins. Place under broiler until slightly browned and bubbly.
Cut into quarters.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions until tender.
Add ground beef and cook until brown. Add all remaining ingredients.
Cook at simmering temperature 1 1/2 to 4 hours.
Serve over 8 ounces cooked spaghetti.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put on a cookie sheet and put in refrigerator to cool overnight or several hours.
Slice into two loaves.
Bake on cookie sheet 1 hour at 350°.

title: pawpaw pie
directions: Peel and remove seeds.
Cook in open kettle with other ingredients until thick. Put in an unbaked crust and bake until crust is baked.
Cover with a meringue and brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook (or steam) the broccoli for 5 or 6 minutes; drain well. Combine soup with the mayonnaise, eggs and cheese.
Add onion; mix well.
Pepper to taste.
Add broccoli; mix well.
Spray a casserole dish with cooking spray.
Pour in mixture.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Top with margarine.
Bake for about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sweet and crunchy nuts
directions: Spray 2 cookie sheets with Pam.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar, salt, butter and sherry.
Blend.
Add nuts and toss to coat well.
Spread on cookie sheets.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 250° until coating and nuts appear dry.
Stir every fifteen minutes to separate nuts.
Rinse off "stickiness" from spatula after each turning.
Cool.
Dry.
Store in tight tins. (Addictive!)

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook both packages of carrots until tender.
Do not overcook. Drain carrots and mix with onions and peppers.
Combine remaining ingredients to create the sauce.
Pour sauce over carrot mixture and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Select large mild onions.
Slice them thin and separate into rings.
Combine milk and eggs in shallow pan.
Dip onion rings into it and make sure each is wet.
Lift onion rings out; coat with flour.
Fry in deep fat until light golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with salt.

title: mozzarella meat pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato paste, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings.
Mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in 9-inch pie plate, pressing together to form crust.
Flute edge.
Fill with meat mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: little cheddar loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine the ground beef, eggs and crackers.
Mix soup mix and milk; then add.
Shape into two loaves in shallow baking dish; bake 1 hour.

title: v.b.s.  cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Roll in coconut.
Store or eat right away.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together eggs, oil and carrots.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: marinara sauce by miriam
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Place plum tomatoes in blender and blend so there are some pieces; do not puree.
Add this and add other ingredients to pan.
Cook 2 hours on low heat.
This sauce is delicious over any variety of pasta and is also wonderful with Veal or Chicken Parmigiana and Chicken Cacciatore*.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mash avocado with fork, then mix with all other ingredients. Layer in pan.
Second layer, green onion (chopped).
Third layer, lettuce (chopped fine).
Fourth layer, tomatoes and fifth layer is Cheddar cheese.
On the second through fifth layers, you can use your own desired amount of each.
Then sprinkle with chili powder.

title: carolyn's pie crust
directions: Blend shortening and butter into flour and salt with pastry cutter till crumbly.
Add cold water, 1 T at a time until dough is formed.
Roll out between sheets of waxed paper and lay in pie plate.
Prick sides with a fork.
Bake 1 crust pie shells for 10 minutes at 425 F.
Bake 2 crust pies at 425 F for 45 minutes. Before baking 2 crust pie, brush top lightly with milk and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl beat shortening, sugar, water and vanilla until well blended.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda.
Gradually add to sugar mixture until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on foil paper.
Remove to rack and completely cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine milk and instant pudding according to package directions.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: spice cake
directions: Sift together flour and spices.
Cream together shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake in 350° oven about 25 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes before removing.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook noodles.
Chop tomatoes, onion and green peppers.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve chilled.

title: spinach in a bread basket
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours to allow flavors to blend.
Prior to serving, cut the top off a round loaf of sourdough bread.
Hollow out the inside and fill with spinach mixture just prior to serving.
Serve with cubes of sourdough bread.

title: turkey tortilla soup(serves 8)
directions: In 5-quart saucepan over medium heat, saute onion in oil 3 to 4 minutes or until translucent. Stir in chilies and taco seasoning mix. Cook 1 minute. Add tomatoes, breaking up with a spoon. Stir in turkey broth; bring to a boil. Add corn and turkey; reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes. Add cilantro.

title: cherry fruit fluff
directions: Mix together pie filling, pineapple and milk plus marshmallows if using; fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry vanilla shortcut
directions: Combine milk and pudding in large bowl. Beat with wire whisk until well blended. Gently stir in 1 cup of whipped topping. Layer pound cake, strawberries and pudding. Top with additional cake, strawberries and whipped topping.

title: "stuff"
directions: Layer first four ingredients in a greased crock-pot.
Add mushroom soup.
Turn on high until it goes to cooking, then turn down until it is done.
Cook two to three hours.
Leftovers, very good the next day!

title: hot artichoke puffs
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar; stir until sugar is dissolved with Jell-O.
Allow to stand until syrupy.
Mash the cheese; add to Jell-O and stir until mixture is creamy.
Whip Dream Whip and fold into Jell-O mixture.
Add pineapple chunks and nuts.
Pour into deep bowl or mold and chill.
Can use cherries to decorate if desired.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order given, adding mayonnaise or dressing on top.
Chill 8 to 12 hours.
Serve.

title: taco shells
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and shortening together with spoon.
Add 2 scant cups of hot water. Mix until a ball forms. Take a portion and roll very thin (1/8 inch).

title: green spaghetti sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add basil and parsley.
Blend in cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, olive oil, garlic and pepper.
Stir in boiling water.
Blend.
Serve with thin spaghetti, Parmesan cheese and a crisp salad.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar with flour and butter.
Add eggs, buttermilk and coconut.
Mix well and pour in shell.
Bake at 300° to 325° until done.

title: hash brown pie
directions: Press hash browns between paper towel to remove excess moisture.
Press into the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: no egg meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly mix all ingredients and shape into a loaf pan.
Bake 90 to 120 minutes.
Drain and remove from loaf pan.
Add additional picante sauce to each serving, if desired.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Stir in soup, thyme and extra vegetables.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Spread potatoes evenly over meat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot all the way through.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat until melted.

title: apple cake(jabkowy placek)
directions: Mix eggs, margarine, sugar, sour cream, soda, baking powder and vanilla until smooth.
Add chopped apples and mix.
Last, add 2 cups of flour and mix well.
Pour in Pyrex baking pan, 8 x 12-inch or similar pan.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, salt and pepper until done.
Drain the fat and mix with taco seasoning and refried beans.
Spread in a casserole pan 1/2-inch deep.

title: chicken breasts in garden sauce
directions: Melt butter and cook chicken breasts over low heat, turning frequently, for 30 minutes until tender.
Keep warm in same skillet.

title: microwave flounder with shrimp sauce
directions: Roll up fillets and arrange, seam side down, in square baking dish.
Combine soup, wine and cheese; spoon over fillets.
Heat, covered, 11 to 12 minutes, until fish is done.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving. Yields 4 servings.

title: ham balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Using a 1/3-cup measure, shape mixture into 2-inch balls.
Place in 2 large, shallow roasting pans.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour over balls.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, basting frequently with sauce.
Yields 15 servings.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Allow cheese to soften at room temperature.
Gradually add drained pineapple, green pepper, onion, pimento and salt.
Chill 24 hours.
Roll cheese mix into ball and in parsley flakes. Freezes well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix the cream cheese, beef and green onion.
Roll into a ball and roll in pecans.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Stir seasonings into pumpkin and add to creamed mixture.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture, then add raisins and nuts; beat.
Drop from spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add flour and baking powder to the creamed mixture.
Then add vanilla and lemon extract and beat again to make sure all ingredients are thoroughly mixed.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and zucchini.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Frost with Frosting to follow.

title: lemon dill potatoes
directions: Scrub and bake potatoes in a 425° oven until tender.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out each potato half, leaving a thin shell.
Place potato pulp into mixing bowl.
Add 3 tablespoons of the melted butter.
Add rest of the ingredients. Beat until smooth.
Pile mixture into shells.
Place in baking pan.
Brush tops with remaining melted butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 425° about 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in order in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour margarine evenly over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool. Serve plain, with Cool Whip or with ice cream.

title: lemon cheese dessert
directions: Make crust in 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Mix crumbs, butter and sugar (reserve 1/2 cup mixture).
Press in bottom and sides of pan.

title: garlic pecans
directions: Place pecans on foil-lined large cookie sheet.
Dot with margarine.
Cook at 300° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and let cool.
Can freeze.
Do not add garlic salt until end of cooking.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients; add dates and nuts.
Add alternately with applesauce to butter and sugar mixture.
Mix thoroughly and pour into well greased 9-inch tube pan and bake at 225° for 1 hour.

title: oriental garden rice
directions: Preheat a large skillet over highest heat until very hot.
Add oil and scrambled eggs.
Add cooked rice and vegetables.
Stir and toss to blend quickly.
Add sesame oil and soy sauce and optional ingredients, if desired.
